title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(Can be prepared a day in advance.)

title: steak soup
directions: Brown steak in butter. Add salt, pepper, celery and onion. Cook until onion is transparent. Add consomme and water. Simmer 30 minutes. Add potatoes and simmer another 30 minutes.

title: beef enchiladas ol
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Stir in 1/2 cup of the salsa and 1/2 of the Velveeta. Cook and stir on medium-low heat until Velveeta is melted. Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture in center of each tortilla. Roll up. Place tortillas, seam-side down, in microwavable baking dish. Top with remaining 1/2 cup salsa and Velveeta. Cover loosely with microwavable plastic wrap. Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes or until Velveeta is melted. Makes 5 servings.

title: hawaiian baked beans and franks
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine pineapple with remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix bread, oleo, salt and onion. Add chicken. Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Pour gravy over it. Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in large skillet and drain off grease.
Add soup, water, corn or vegetables, green pepper and chili powder.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients well; spoon on top of meat mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°, until brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain and mash potatoes.
Add margarine and eggs.
Mix well.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Add cinnamon if desired.
Cook in pie shells at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Cook noodles.
Drain hamburger meat; add both soups and add Veg-All after you drain it.
Combine with noodles.
Sprinkle cheeses over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator for at least 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pineapple, pie filling, then dry cake mix into pan.
Place chopped nuts on next with margarine slices as top layer.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes, or until nuts and cake mix are nicely browned.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or a dollop of Cool Whip.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Boil together the first 5 ingredients until sugar dissolves, approximately 4 minutes. Cool.
Combine the cabbage and salt.
Mix and let stand at room temperature.
Squeeze cabbage.
Add some cold water and squeeze again.
Chop the onion.
Let stand in vinegar while mixing other ingredients.
Chop the celery and green pepper.
Mix and store in refrigerator until used.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and pull apart. Saute in butter until soft but not brown. Roll out crackers and put in skillet with melted butter.
Layer buttered crumbs, onions and grated cheese in casserole, ending with crumbs on top.
Sprinkle canned milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan.
Saute garlic and onion for 4 minutes.
Process undrained tomatoes, green pepper and celery in blender until smooth.
Stir into onion mixture.
Add kidney beans, garbanzo beans and chili peppers.
Mix vinegar, chili powder, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Add to tomato mixture with basil, oregano, cumin, allspice and bay leaf.
Stir in beer.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally and adding water for desired consistency.
Remove bay leaf. Serve sprinkled with cheese.

title: potato pork casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown chops on both sides in 10-inch skillet. Pour off drippings. Mix next 6 ingredients. Pour half in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange potatoes in pan.
Top with pork chops. Top with remaining soup mixture. Cover and bake 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: easy date nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Rice Krispies, vanilla and powdered sugar or coconut) and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Mix well.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar or fine coconut. Will make 5 to 6 dozen and will keep a very long time, if put in a tin box with a tight lid.

title: not-so-sloppy joes
directions: Add all ingredients (except hamburger buns).
Simmer until brown.
Spoon over hamburger buns and serve with milk.

title: lazy man's pierogi
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon and fry onions until clear, not brown.
Saute mushrooms in a little butter.
Rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Combine bacon, onion, mushrooms and sauerkraut with undiluted mushroom soup.
Cook macaroni; do not overcook.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter, chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time and beat 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour in cool pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flavoring and buttermilk.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: glorified chuck roast
directions: Place meat on heavy foil; pour cream of mushroom soup over meat and sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top.
Wrap all ingredients in foil and seal edges with double fold.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Roast in preheated 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Loosen foil and brown for about 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Use the juices for gravy.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let sit for 2 hours.
Prepare a well in middle of bread loaf (removed bread cut in cubes).
Place spinach dip in well.
Place cubes around bread.
Dip cubes into center when complete and tear bread from loaf.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat quickly in shortening; add onions and mushrooms. Cook until tender, then add beef broth and sour cream and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over buttered egg noodles or rice.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients thoroughly and roll into balls. Roll each ball into the additional pecans and serve with crackers or celery.

title: red green casserole
directions: Heat beans.
Mix all other ingredients and sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Makes a beautiful red/green dish.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Fry meat and onion; season.
Grate cheese.
Warm tortillas to soften.
Take tortillas and place meat into the middle.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll up and place in pan.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients (first 8 ingredients).
Spread on each tortilla.
Roll into a roll and cut 3/4 strips.
(Wonderful company appetizers.)

title: people biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir the shortening and cheese into the biscuit mix.
Add the milk.
Stir together with a fork.
Beat 15 strokes.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Drop the mix by tablespoonful onto the sheet.
Put the biscuits in the oven.
Remove after 12 to 15 minutes.

title: steak rolls and noodles
directions: Lay steaks out on a flat surface.
Season with steak seasoning, seasoned salt and red pepper.
Chop parsley and place a layer on each steak.
Peel cloves of garlic.
Slice each clove three ways the long way.
Spread slices from one clove on each steak.
Grab each steak at the end and roll it like a jelly roll.
Season the outside of each roll.
Pour white wine in a medium-sized frying pan.
Turn heat on medium.
Place steaks in wine.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Put in well-greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Put on top of first mixture.
Cook at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes to one hour. Very good!!!

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble wafers real fine.
Chop dates and add to crumbs; mix well.
Add fruit mix, nuts and raisins and mix well.
Then add milk and mix well.
Put in icebox to set.

title: green bean and onion ring casserole
directions: Cook green beans and onion in saucepan on stove top until onion is tender.
Drain beans.
Cut ham and cheese into narrow 3/4-inch wedges.
Combine beans, ham, cheese and soup in greased wide shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange onion rings on top. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Soak in cold water overnight.
Cook until tender.
Cook ham hocks until done; remove from broth. Bone, then chop meat coarsely.
Drain beans and add to ham broth along with celery, carrots and onion and cook until done.
Add water as needed.
Rub egg into flour to make rivels; add to soup and cook another 10 minutes.
Rivels are optional.
Also canned beans may be used instead of dry beans.
Add meat to soup and heat.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; let stand until bubbly.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and potatoes.
Mix in flour, a cup at a time.
Add yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to handle easily.
Put in a greased bowl, cover with plastic wrap and let set overnight or until ready to make rolls.
Make sure bowl is large enough as it will double in volume.
May keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Remove dough 2 hours before you wish to use it for biscuits.
Shape rolls (I use a glass to cut out rolls).
Let rise on cookie sheet until double, covered with a towel.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ruth mihachik's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
This is very important!
Cook just until soft ball is formed when tested in water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Add nuts if desired.
Beat until all ingredients are well mixed and candy is slightly thick.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch buttered pan.
(Hardens slowly.)

title: peach or apple crumb pie
directions: Mix all together and put in an unbaked pie shell.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in an unbaked pie shell. Makes 2 pies.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together, except for fruit, for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased pan, then arrange fruit on top.

title: julia's dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding egg whites last.
Spread mixture about 1/2-inch thick in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool.
On the day dessert is served, break 1/2 of cake into small pieces.
Arrange on cake plate.
Top this with fruits as desired (bananas, peaches, fruit for salad, etc.)
Break remainder of cake over top.
Pour over all a can of crushed pineapple.
Spread with whipped cream and garnish with cherries.

title: pralines #2
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Cool to 220°.
Beat.
Add pecans and pour out by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: zucchini-vegetable soup
directions: Place all raw vegetables in saucepan with approximately 1 1/2 cups water; add seasonings.
Simmer together until vegetables are done (about 30 minutes).
Add 1 cup cheese and simmer 5 minutes. Serve with extra cheese sprinkled on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Pour mixture over chicken, placed in single layers, skin side up in shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, basting occasionally.

title: bubbles
directions: Combine and shake well. Let settle for 4 hours.
Keep covered. Use for any bubble wand or toy.

title: herb-stuffed turkey breast
directions: Place turkey breast, skin side down.
Spread cut surfaces with mustard.
Top with bacon, thyme and parsley.
Fold long sides of breast over stuffing so they overlap slightly.
Skewer or tie to hold sides together.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: polka-dotted macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni as directed on package.
Empty into bowl the Cheddar cheese soup.
Slowly stir in milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread drained macaroni in baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inches.
Then pour cheese sauce over macaroni, stirring to mix.
Cut hot dogs into penny-thin slices.
Arrange hot dog slices on top of macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with sliced green onions and chopped tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie shell.
(Don't use an electric mixer.)
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Blend shortening with sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Gradually add flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until light brown for about 10 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add flour, meal, broccoli, and cheese, coating broccoli and cheese.
Beat eggs well, adding buttermilk, and oil.
Add broccoli mixture.
Bake in greased and floured skillet or pan at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: simple chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in the bottom of dish. Cover with chopped eggs. Mix soups and broth and pour over chicken and eggs.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until tender.
Cool. Alternate layer of carrots, bell pepper and onion slices in dish. Make marinade of remaining ingredients, beating well until completely blended.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate. Will keep for several weeks.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Crush cookies and press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Freeze for 30 minutes.
Put softened ice cream into the pie crust; freeze until hard.
Smooth chocolate fudge topping over ice cream; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Return to freezer.
When firm, top with Cool Whip and grate chocolate bar over the top.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in order in a jar; leave the clove of garlic in the jar.
Shake well.

title: pear honey
directions: Let sugar-pear mixture set overnight.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add small jar maraschino cherries, chopped fine.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar.
Press into large glass dish. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour over pretzels.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add strawberries.
Pour over top. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Rinse rice, then spread in pan.
Layer chicken, then cream of chicken soup. Add water.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple apricot dessert
directions: Combine jello and undrained pineapple in saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until it reaches the simmering point.
Add sugar, apricot baby food and cream cheese.
Chill until mixture mounds from the spoon.
Whip chilled milk; blend in lemon juice. Beat until stiff.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Turn into lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with nuts.

title: wine jelly
directions: Stir the sugar into the wine and warm in a stainless steel pan until the sugar is dissolved.
Do not overheat.
It must not quite come to the simmer.
Remove from heat and stir in pectin, being very careful to dissolve the pectin completely in the sugar and wine mixture.
Pour into small 8 ounce jelly glass jars.
Keep refrigerated. Keeps 2 months.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and all ingredients into a blender.
Let chill overnight.
Roll into ball and roll in nuts, parsley or paprika.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Brush eggplant with oil.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes. Saute onions, garlic and ground beef.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, salt and pepper.
Layer eggplant and meat in casserole; top with Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese or pizza cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven. During last 15 minutes, uncover and sprinkle with cornflake crumbs and melted butter. Great for church potluck.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into casserole (2-quart) and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer bar cookies
directions: Melt butter in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Layer with chocolate bits, butterscotch bits, coconut and nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mrs. hoover's sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together with half of flour.
Then add the rest of the flour.
Bake at 400° to 450°.
Yield 60 to 90 cookies.

title: tena's mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° until lightly browned.

title: new england hot punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and simmer 30 minutes.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: In 2 1/2-quart baking dish, combine beans, corn, chestnuts and onions.
In medium bowl, combine soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into vegetables and stir lightly to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
In small bowl, combine cracker crumbs, almonds and butter. Sprinkle over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is lightly browned and bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple apricot salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar and cream cheese.
Bring to a boil; stir well.
Add gelatin and water.
Refrigerate until partly set.
Add Cool Whip.
Let stand in refrigerator until set.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening; mix. Add sugar, salt and eggs slightly beaten; mix. Dissolve 2 packages dry yeast in 1 cup warm water. Add to liquids. Stir in 6 cups (or less) flour gradually; set aside in warm place to rise until double in bulk, approximately 50 to 60 minutes, then roll out as for biscuits. Cut with biscuit cutter. Turn in melted butter and stack in Bundt pans. They'll be about 1/3 full. Let rise until double in bulk (40 to 50 minutes).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all together except for the nuts.
Shape into a log. Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill well and serve with crackers.
This is good to serve at parties, or social gatherings.
It is easy and inexpensive to make.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone; layer chicken, onion and Doritos. Pour warmed mixture of tomatoes and soups over the layers.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into creamed mixture.
Mix.
Roll into balls; flatten with glass bottom dropped in sugar.
Top with a pecan half.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all together, except potato sticks.
Just before serving, add can of potato sticks.
Crunchy, different and delicious! Serve on lettuce bed or with tomatoes.

title: garden chicken stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and cook chicken with vegetables over medium-high heat, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until chicken is golden and vegetables are crisp-tender.
Blend Cup-a-Soup with water; add to skillet.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: fried mud fish
directions: Keep fillets cold on ice while preparing.
Mix corn meal and flour.
Cut fillets into strips across the fillet about 1/4 inch thick.
Place in ice water while preparing.
When ready to cook, drain.
Salt with garlic and pepper salt.
Roll in yellow mustard, then in corn meal and flour mixture.
Drop pieces into hot oil until golden brown.
Take up and eat.
Delicious with honey mustard sauce.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and pineapple; mix thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop onto greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine the milk and egg.
Stir this mixture into the contents of the bowl.
Mix thoroughly and bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dream of hawaii meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, eggs, 2 teaspoons salt and pepper. Shape into about 32 meatballs. Dip in soy sauce.
Cook in small amount of oil in large skillet until browned on all sides. Remove from skillet to 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: pasta primavera with cheese
directions: In large saucepan cook zucchini, carrot, onion, mushrooms and garlic in butter until just tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add flour, blend well.
Gradually stir in evaporated skimmed milk. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Season with basil, salt and pepper.
Add the cheese; cook, stirring, until melted.
Add the broccoli, toss in the drained pasta.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked carrot squares(diet)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in buttered baking dish (8 inches square).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 9 squares.

title: irish tony's italian soup
directions: Saute sausage, breaking up into small pieces.
Add onions and garlic and cook for 3-4 minutes.
Drain fat if necessary.
Add beef broth, tomatoes, wine, sugar, herbs.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and bring back to a boil.
Break pasta into 2 inch lengths and add. Simmer 10-15 minutes.
Add chicken broth if more liquid is desired.
If bouillon cubes are used, add 2 c. water. Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning, sour cream and cream cheese until smooth. Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Spread on large pizza pan or two small 9-inch pie plates.
Top with liquid taco sauce.
Layer lettuce, cucumber, tomato, onion and Cheddar cheese in this order.
Serve with nacho tortilla chips.

title: it's good for your kid candy
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pat mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill and cut into small squares.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry, except bake 5 minutes before filling.
Carefully easy pastry back into dish if necessary.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Beat eggs and vanilla with hand beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into partially baked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted half way from center of filling comes out clean. Cool slightly.
Serve warm or refrigerate until serving time. Makes 8 servings.

title: microwave frosted peanut marshmallow crispy treats
directions: Microwave margarine in a large mixing bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows and toss to coat. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Blend in peanut butter.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add butter, milk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: potato-mushroom soup
directions: Cook potatoes with mushrooms in 1 1/4 quarts water with salt. While potatoes are cooking, mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup together.
When potatoes are done, add sour cream mixture to potatoes and water.
Stir thoroughly.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Add pepper to taste.
Pour small amount at a time in blender and blend until smooth.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and remove from bones in small pieces.
In baking dish, put layer of chicken, layer of stuffing and repeat until it's all done.
Heat other ingredients in saucepan; stir well.
Pour over chicken and stuffing.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli angelina
directions: Cook
broccoli	according to package directions.
Drain water from broccoli;
add butter and cream cheese to broccoli and heat until melted.
Add chopped water chestnuts to broccoli
mixture. Line a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with artichoke hearts.
Pour broccoli mixture over artichoke hearts.
Sprinkle
Parmesan cheese over broccoli.
Pour bread crumbs on top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well with hand mixer.
Blend in milk and flavorings.
Drain cherries really well by pressing between paper towels to remove excess juice.
Shape a small amount of mixture around each cherry.
Place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate morsels.
Spread evenly in a well-greased baking pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle top with remaining chocolate morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes or until chocolate morsels are soft enough to spread over top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: turtle ice cream bars
directions: In a bowl combine caramel topping, chocolate chips and pecans. Spread in bottom of frozen pie crust.

title: herbed roast beef in salt crust
directions: Combine oil, onion, garlic salt, basil, marjoram, thyme and pepper in a heavy plastic bag. Mix well. Add roast; coat well with marinade. Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight. Line roasting pan with foil. Combine coarse kosher salt and water to form a thick slush. Pat 1 cup of mixture into a 1/2-inch-thick rectangle in pan. Pat roast dry with paper towels. Insert meat thermometer. Place roast on salt layer. Pack remaining salt mixture around meat to seal well. Place roast in a 425 degree oven and roast 16 to 18 minutes per pound for rare (140 degrees), 20 to 22 minutes per pound for medium (160 degrees) or 25 to 30 minutes for well done (170 degree). Remove roast when thermometer registers 5 degrees

below desired doneness. Let roast stand 5 to 10 minutes in salt crust. To remove crust, you may need to use a hammer. After removing crust, whisk away any remaining salt crystals on roast with a pastry brush.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Use a mixer to combine all ingredients.
Let it set a day or two.
Optional:
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: sugar free cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple well. Fold in sour cream. You can add walnut bits. Put in a pie crust and chill. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pear preserves
directions: Pare fruit (if hard, cook until tender in water).
Make syrup of liquid and sugar; add fruit to partly cooled syrup and bring gently to boil.
Add lemon.
Boil rapidly until clear and tender. Let stand in syrup to cool.
Reheat syrup to boiling.
Pour fruit and boiling syrup into jars within 1/2 inch from top.
Put caps, screw lids firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yields 10 (8 ounce) jars.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage together.
Add to cheese, that has been melted (microwave or slow cooker).
Add mushroom soup (this helps so that the cheese will not stick to the boiler).
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Serve hot from a crock-pot.
Great with chips and perfect for parties.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with melted margarine and broth.
Put 1/2 in baking dish.
Mix onion, celery, chicken, mayonnaise and salt together; pour over dressing.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and pour over the chicken mixture.
Add second half of dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking and spread soup on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese; bake 10 minutes more.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together and add enough water to make 2 1/2 gallons.
Put in freezer 24 hours before serving time.
Keep stirred so it will be slushy when ready to serve.
Add one or two bottles of ginger ale at serving time for the desired consistency.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil well, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Beat in the vinegar and food coloring.
Sift flour with soda and cocoa, then add the flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to the egg mixture.
Stir in one teaspoon of vanilla. Blend thoroughly and pour into 2 greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frosty date balls
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar together.
Stir in water, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in the dates and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until set but not brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: egg omelet
directions: Mix in a microwave-safe bowl sprayed with Crisco butter spray, 2 eggs and beat well.
Add a tablespoon of milk.
Add a teaspoon of diced green peppers, a teaspoon of diced onions and any kind of diced meat if desired.
Add two slices of American cheese, broken into pieces.
Mix ingredients well.
Cook in microwave oven for approximately 2 minutes on High.
Take bowl out of microwave, stir and let cool for about 1 minute.
Put egg mix back in the microwave for approximately a minute until cooked.
Serve with toast.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add boiling water (1/2 cup), mix well and add other ingredients.
Stir occasionally until mixture begins to thicken. Pour in mold and let congeal.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cream margarine and softened cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar, evaporated milk, baking cocoa and vanilla; beat well.
Yield:
Enough for 1 cake, 12 servings.

title: honey whole wheat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in honey, shortening, salt, 1 3/4 cup warm water and the whole wheat flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough all-purpose white flour to make the dough easy to handle.
(Should not be sticky.)

title: sea side sizzler
directions: Mix in order.
Spread on English muffin halves or sourdough slices.
Heat under broiler and serve hot.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add sugar and salt.
Cut in oleo or butter with a pastry blender to consistency of coarse meal.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Add molasses and egg and blend well.
Pour 1/2 of the liquid mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/4 of flour mix over liquid.
Stir very gently. Pour in remaining liquid.
Top with rest of flour mix.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake until filling is set and crust golden.

title: grandma godfrey's sugar cookies(100 years old)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Gradually add eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Thinly slice all vegetables.
Pan-fry in a little oil until crisp-tender.
Add soy sauce (about 1 to 2 tablespoons).
Continue to pan-fry until soy sauce is evaporated.

title: pican-toes
directions: Slice potatoes in a 2-cup microwave casserole.
Cover with lid, cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes, or until tender, stirring once.
Top with picante sauce and cheese.
Cover until cheese is melted.
Serves 2.

title: dulco de nuez
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, corn syrup and soda in large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and add pecans. Cook and stir until mixture reaches soft ball stage (328°). Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. When cool, store in airtight container.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening and butter. Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin and egg.
Add all dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake on ungreased and floured cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes. Refrigerate dough between bakings.
Drop by spoon.

title: ham filling for florida celery fingers
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Use to fill Florida celery fingers.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat all ingredients, except pepperoni and cheese, until smooth.
Add pepperoni and cheese.
Pour into 8-inch greased square pan and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes and cut into squares.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir well.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut brittle (with salted peanuts)
directions: Stir together the sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to 280°.
Stir in peanuts gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly until 300°.
Add baking soda; stir gently but quickly.
Pour onto 2 greased cookie sheets without spreading.
Cool; break into pieces when cold.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, vinegar and food coloring. Slowly add flour and cocoa alternating with milk.
Bake in two greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda into a medium sized mixing bowl and set aside.
Put butter or margarine into a large mixing bowl and cream it well, then add sugar, a little at a time, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat the eggs in small bowl.
Add the beaten eggs to butter and sugar mixture.
Add milk and sifted dry ingredients to egg, butter and sugar mixture.
Stir.
Combine sugar and cinnamon for topping. Drop large teaspoonfuls of dough onto greased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on the top.
Bake about 10 minutes until cookies brown around the edges.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt cocoa and margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugar and eggs.
Add salt, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on hot cake.
Spread with chocolate icing.

title: rotelle salad
directions: Cook macaroni al dente!
Drain and rinse with cold water. Place in large bowl and add rest of the ingredients; toss.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Place ham and cheese over bottom half of rolls and top with other half of rolls.
Return to pans.
Mix melted margarine, Worcestershire sauce, onion, mustard and poppy seed together. Pour over the rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes until heated through.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into a large microwave safe bowl (do not mix).
Place in microwave on high for 3 minutes.
remove from microwave, add the rest of the ingredients except nuts and stir to remove all lumps, add nuts if desired.

title: pearl's cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time.
Add flour slowly until blended.
Add vanilla and lemon extract. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly.
Lightly score top of batter with knife into about 18 squares.
Place a teaspoon or more of cherry filling at each line intersection.
Use all filling.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: shrimp rice
directions: Melt margarine in pot.
Add onion, bell pepper and pimentos; saute until tender.
Add shrimp; stir until pink.
Add beef consomme, then rice.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to medium-low until rice is tender.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Simmer in skillet for 10 minutes. Combine all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon macaroon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly. Add the melted butter, sugar, salt, vanilla and lemon juice. Beat until well blended. Stir in coconut.
Pour the filling into the crust. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until the top is browned and the filling is set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of the butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix gently until blended.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 portions.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Mix together the Veg-All mix, 1 cup shredded cheese, mayo, water chestnuts and small onion in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 stick melted butter or margarine and 1 cup cracker crumbs to mixture. After mixing, pour in baking dish and sprinkle the remaining 1 cup of cracker crumbs on top.
Put in oven and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: In a blender, combine dry milk, sugar, boiling water and margarine. Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator. Use in any recipe calling for sweetened condensed milk.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients until blended.
Spoon into paper muffin cups.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 35 minutes).
Makes about 36 to 40 mini muffins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen raspberries; mix until thawed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onion, garlic and peppers.
Add water and bring to a boil, then add cornmeal and beans with liquid.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mom's gingerbread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine the brown sugar, molasses and melted butter.
Add the eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to the sugar, molasses, butter and eggs mixture.
Mix well.
Add the boiling water and mix thoroughly.
Transfer the batter to the prepared pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Cool.
Yield: 8 to 10 squares.

title: dorothy's fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken in
salt water.
Drain slightly.
Shake in a bag or covered dish with Shake 'n Bake, cornflake crumbs and all-purpose batter.
Brown	chicken in Crisco oil.	Season and place
in flat pan.
Sprinkle
with
onion	flakes.
Add
some water and cover with foil.	Bake
1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and continue to bake until done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line cookie sheet with rolls, making an edge like a pizza. Make sure to spray pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool. Mix cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise with Ranch dressing until soft enough to spread.
Spread cream cheese mixture into cooled crust.
Layer vegetables on top with grated cheese and olives.

title: orange flavored beef short ribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Make two vertical deep cuts into meat on each rib.
In Dutch oven or 4-quart saucepan, mix beef ribs, tomato juice, brown sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.

title: creamed potatoes(125 calories per serving)
directions: In large saucepan over high heat, heat all ingredients but cornstarch to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
In cup, stir cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water until smooth; stir into potato mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lo-fat pizza casserole(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: english muffin bread(microwave with changes for oven)
directions: Don't throw
away egg yolks when just using the whites. Freeze the yolks in ice cube trays.
When frozen, take out and put in
a plastic bag and store in freezer.
When baking cakes or cookies, 2 thawed egg yolks and 1 tablespoon water, equals 1 egg.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling pineapple.
Add buttermilk; let set in refrigerator for 45 minutes.
Remove; add Cool Whip and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish; chill until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.
Chill.
Slice and serve.

title: instant breakfast drink
directions: Pour ingredients into blender.
Mix for 1 minute.
Pour into glasses.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chocolate cake with caramel frosting
directions: Cream Crisco and brown sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Mix in vanilla extract and melted chocolate until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add with buttermilk alternately until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: chicken and veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
(Drain mixed vegetables and use broth from chicken to moisten vegetables.)

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl and add 1 egg at a time, mixing well.
Add lemon and vanilla flavoring.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Alternate, adding buttermilk and dry mixture to creamed butter, egg and sugar mixture.
Pour into a buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 3/4 hours, checking for doneness with toothpick.
Start checking at 1 hour.

title: best ever hot fudge sauce(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass dish, measure all ingredients except vanilla. Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir until smooth. Cook 4 to 5 minutes until thickened. Add vanilla, stirring until smooth and glossy. Serve hot.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: easy pizza
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain it.
Lay the biscuits in a cake pan, side by side.
Cover with pizza sauce, hamburger and cheese. Bake, using biscuit directions.
Cut and serve.
Add other toppings to your taste.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and 1 cup flour.
Beat well and add soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat well again.
Then add nuts, apple and rest of flour.
Stir by hand.
Grease tube pan with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with glaze, if desired.

title: ham and vegetable medley
directions: With sharp knife, cut ham into 1/4-inch thick strips about 3-inches long, cut each tomato into 8 wedges, cut green and red peppers into 1/2-inch wide strips, cut onion, yellow squash and zucchini into 1/4-inch wide slices.
In 12-inch skillet over high heat, heat salad oil; cook green and red peppers, onion, yellow squash, zucchini and ham about 5 minutes, stir frequently.
Reduce heat to medium, add water, chicken broth, basil, salt and pepper. Cook until vegies are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato wedges, continue cooking until tomatoes are heated through.

title: aunt peg's wassail
directions: Heat as you mix the first 7 ingredients (do not use an aluminum pan).
Bring to a boil and strain.
Add the cider and juices.
Keep heated as you serve.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Form mixture into large plump patties.
Brown in butter, in large frying pan.
Pour off grease. Pour soup and water over patties and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole(simmer pot, microwave clay pot)
directions: Soak simmer pot as instructed for 10 minutes.
Crumble sausage in bottom half of simmer pot.
Cook for 5 minutes on High, stirring halfway through cook period.
Add vegetables.
Cook 5 minutes on High, stirring once or twice.
Drain excess fat.

title: summer pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add lemon juice and water or ice cubes.
Let thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350° (325° if using glass baking dish). Microwave chocolate and margarine in large micro-proof bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add beef and cook until well browned.
Drain off fat; stir in seasoning mix, following package directions.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, alternate thin layers of meat, cheese and corn chips.
Repeat until all is used, ending with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve on a bed of shredded lettuce, chopped tomato, sour cream and taco sauce.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add bananas and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture alternately with milk.
Stir after each addition.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Use 9 x 5-inch bread pan or 2 large size foil pans.
Decrease time to 45 minutes if using 2 pans.

title: crab pizza
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Spread on plate or on pizza pan. Combine chili sauce, horseradish and crab meat.
Spread crab mixture on cheese mixture and refrigerate. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook pie shell for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Cook sausage and drain.
Grate cheese.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie shell.
Cook in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs. Add all ingredients in saucepan. Bring just to a boil. Sprinkle with nutmeg after pouring into bowl. Cool.

title: ham fettucine
directions: Prepare fettucine according to package directions.
While fettucine is cooking, cook green peas.
Set aside.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar. Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and cool. Add powdered sugar until right consistency to spread.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 1/2-inch pie plate (glass works best).
Cook broccoli.
Mix other ingredients together. Pour over broccoli placed in pie plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand prior to cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers (better second day).

title: very good baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together as a spread for crackers or chips.
Very good.

title: tomato drink
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Simmer until hot.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Brown onions in fat; add celery and bell pepper.
Season shrimp and add to vegetables.
Brown all.
Add 2 quarts of water and continue cooking until shrimp and vegetables are tender.
Stir in onion soup mix and soup.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes.
Add onion tops, parsley and rice. Bring to a full boil.
Stir and simmer, until rice is cooked. Serves 6 to 12.

title: raw cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries.
Chop the oranges and add to the cranberries.
Add orange juice and sugar and mix well. Refrigerate 24 hours prior to serving.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Place 8 slices of bread, cut in cubes, in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown and drain sausage; crumble over bread cubes. Grate 3/4 pound cheese over sausage and bread.
Beat the eggs, milk and dry mustard together.
Pour over casserole.
Spread 1 can cream of mushroom soup over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning for 1 hour at 325°.
Perfect for Christmas morning!

title: beef-nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in corn, salsa, mayonnaise and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole dish. Repeat layers.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomato, etc.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients except the whiskey for 1 minute in blender.
Add whiskey and blend 1/2 minute more.
Serve.
Will keep in refrigerator at least 3 weeks.
Freezes well too.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk; mix well. Stir in crabmeat, cheese and onions. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Serves 6.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Gradually add half and half and milk, stirring constantly; cook over low heat until smooth and thickened.
Remove from
heat.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup of cheese.
Stir to blend.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pta mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Break mincemeat into bits and add to creamed mixture with dry ingredients.
Blend, don't beat.
Chill in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls; dip in egg white and sugar.
Bake on greased sheet for 10-12 minutes at 400°.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over corn meal, salt, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add eggs, baking powder and milk.
Mix well.
Melt butter or margarine in casserole and pour in mixture.
Blend in butter. Cook 45 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Mix by hand; flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Blend in beaten eggs and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Stir jellos and marshmallows into water until melted.
Chill until partially set.
Add all other ingredients and fold in. Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: pecan crusted southern fried chicken
directions: Heat oil over medium heat in a large skillet. Ground pecans.

title: summer vegetable spaghetti
directions: Combine the first ten ingredients in a large saucepan; cook for 10 minutes, then stir in tomato paste.

Cover and cook gently, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender. Cook spaghetti in unsalted water according to package directions. Spoon sauce over drained hot spaghetti and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring to a boil in an iron skillet.
Put in a pie pan lined with buttered aluminum foil.
Let harden.
Break into pieces.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In
a large mixing bowl, stir together sugar, flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Remove from mixer. Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).

Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans, 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pans or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans to wire racks.
Cool completely.
(Cake may be left in rectangular pans, if desired.) Frost with One-Bowl Buttercream Frosting.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake cake mix but use milk instead of water.
Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle when done.
Mix pineapple with sugar and pour over cake.
Mix cream cheese and pudding with milk.
Do not cook.
Spread over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Top with cherries and nuts.

title: melting lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two large cookie sheets; set aside.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate.
Drop batter by level teaspoon 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake only 6 at a time. Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven. Let stand 1 minute, then quickly remove to flat surface to cool. Repeat with remaining batter.
Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling, water.
With small knife or spatula, spread the back of one cookie with chocolate and sandwich it with a second cookie. Repeat with remaining cookies and chocolate.
Store in airtight containers or freeze.
Makes 2 dozen.
About 100 calories each.

title: easy cream cheese pinwheels
directions: Blend everything together except tortillas.
Spread mixture over 4 tortillas.
Roll each into a cylinder and slice into pinwheels.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Add beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Add remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg.
Roll chicken in egg and then in crumbs.
Brown chicken and drain off fat.
Stir in soup, water, onion and seasonings.
Cook, covered, on low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: mini crab cake appetizer
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir well.
Add crabmeat, bread crumbs, cilantro and pimento, stirring well.
Shape mix into 24 (2 inch) round patties.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Coat large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add crab cakes in batches and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side until golden.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions; drain.
In a skillet, add onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Cook until beef is brown.
Drain excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, whole tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: angel puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Beat eggs until firm. Add sugar and vanilla. Fold in pecans and chocolate chips. Line cookie sheets with paper. Drop spoonful of mixture on paper. Turn oven off. Put in oven overnight. It is better to make these puff later in the evening so they can be in the oven overnight.

title: dill pickles(polish)
directions: Make brine of 1 cup salt and 3 gallons of water.
Soak cucumbers in brine overnight.
Drain and wipe dry.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix garlic powder, cayenne pepper and dehydrated onion together and sprinkle over roast.
Pour water around roast (as much as possible) and add beef bouillon cubes.
Cover with lid or foil and bake.
Leftover juices can be frozen for future uses such as soups, gravy, for adding to rice, etc.

title: homemade chili
directions: Rinse beans and mushrooms.
Place all ingredients in a microwave container.
Microwave 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir halfway through.
Contains 0 fat.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots; cook in slightly sweetened water.
Remove from heat while still a little crisp; drain.
Slice onions and chop pepper over carrots.
Heat tomato soup, oil, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Do not boil.
Pour over carrot mixture; stir a few times at intervals so it will be evenly marinated.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate crispies
directions: To the melted chocolate, add the sugar, butter, eggs, flour and vanilla; mix well and spread in square pan.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Bake 15 minutes in a hot oven (400°).
Cut into squares when warm.
This makes 2 dozen or more pieces.

title: sausage-egg breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in the bottom of 7 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Drain sausage and sprinkle over bread cubes.
Whip eggs. Add mustard and milk.
Mix well and pour over sausage and bread cubes.
Grate cheese over top.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. May be made as long as 2 days ahead and kept in refrigerator. Great for brunch, served with grits, fruit cup and biscuits.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt
peanut
butter and butter together.
Add powdered sugar. Roll
into
small balls and place on wax paper.
Chill for
to 2 hours.
Stick toothpick in balls.
Melt chocolate chips
and paraffin in double boiler.	Dip balls in chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: quick quiche
directions: In food processor, mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased quiche or pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 34 to 40 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: 24-hour layered salad
directions: In large bowl, layer all but last 3 ingredients.
Repeat layers.
Spread mayonnaise over top and seal to edge of bowl. Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over sugar.
Let chill, covered, for 24 hours.
Toss when ready to serve.
Topping makes dressing.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add egg and milk, beating until smooth.
Heat 1/4 inch of oil to 375° in skillet.
Cover bottom opening of a funnel with finger (3/8-inch works best).
Pour 1/4 cup of batter into funnel.
Hold funnel over center of skillet. Remove finger from end to release batter into hot oil; move funnel in slow circular motion to form a spiral design.
Fry 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon in a heavy saucepan or skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into hot bacon.
Cook over low heat just until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir occasionally, pour over lettuce, dandelion or watercress.

title: cheese bites
directions: Cream cheese and margarine; blend well.
Add flour, rice cereal and garlic powder.
Shape into balls and flatten between fingers.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: tuna-macaroni skillet(beverly slimm)
directions: Mix soup and water in a 10-inch skillet.
Stir in vegetables, macaroni and dill weed.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in tuna and heat until hot, about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions.
Serves 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Combine with soups, broth and green chilies.
Add pieces of chicken and stir well.

title: apple torte
directions: Blend ingredients together and place in greased 9-inch pie tin. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: devil's float
directions: Sift flour, white sugar, salt, 2 teaspoons cocoa and baking powder in 9-inch well-greased pan.
Add nuts; toss lightly.
Blend milk, oleo and vanilla and add to mixture in pan; blend into batter.
Mix brown sugar and remaining cocoa and spread over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream.

title: herbed macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in the flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and all of the Havarti.
Stir until melted.
Pour sauce over macaroni; mix well.

title: onion soup au gratin
directions: In a covered 3-quart saucepan over low heat, in oil and butter, cook onions for 15 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; stir in sugar.
Over medium heat, cook 30 minutes more or until onions are golden, stirring frequently.
Add broth, water and wine.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer for 25 minutes.
Ladle soup into six 12 ounce ovenproof bowls; place on pan. Place bread in each bowl and top with cheese and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until cheese is melted and top is brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine cocoa and butter; melt over low heat.
Remove from heat; mix in sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on hot cake.
Spread with Chocolate Icing.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix, then simmer 15 min. or until tender.

title: death by chocolate pie
directions: Crust:
Crush 1/2 package Nabisco chocolate wafers in a blender.
Add enough softened butter to make the crumbs hold together, press into a 9-inch pie pan and chill.

title: white sauce
directions: In a double boiler (or saucepan over low heat), melt butter; add flour, pepper, salt and paprika and stir until blended smooth. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Makes 1 cup.

title: easy snack
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan; add Worcestershire and Season-All.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cottage cheese pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve 2 boxes jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and stir gently with a spoon.
Grease a pan (whatever size desired).
Pour mixture into pan.
Let set; cut into squares and serve.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine fruit, raisins, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 4 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange washed chicken in greased 12 x 8 x 2 baking dish. Top with cheese slices. Combine soup and milk; stir well. Spoon sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing. Drizzle butter over crumbs. Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes. Yields 6 servings. Freezes well.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots; cook in salt water until tender, but not mushy.
Blend other ingredients.
Drain carrots.
Add onion; cover with sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bubble bread
directions: Place frozen bread in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into cubes and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan the next day.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cubes.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg yolks and vinegar.
Roll nuts and fruit in 1 tablespoon flour.
Add nuts and fruit to mixture. Fold in egg whites that have been beaten stiff.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Melt margarine.
Add coconut and pecans.
Toast until brown, stirring constantly.
Bake two (9-inch) pie crusts.
Layer:
cream cheese mixture, coconut mixture, caramel topping and repeat.

title: mr. salty jello salad
directions: Mix together first three (3) items and spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together the next three (3) items and spread over the pretzel layer that is cool.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Sift and add to first mixture, flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Form into small balls.
Roll balls in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400 F for 8-10 minutes.
Cookie dough may be chilled and kept before rolling into balls for baking.

title: rich peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl over hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: cherry-coke salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add Coke, black cherries and juice and undrained pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: dottie's father's well known candy apples
directions: Insert skewers into stem end of apples.
Combine and boil the water, molasses and cream of tartar to 310° on candy thermometer. Do not stir.
Add red food coloring to boiled ingredients and quickly stir.
Dip apples quickly into hot syrup.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Do not use wax paper.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set. Let cool on rack.

title: cold grapefruit nog
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in grapefruit juice.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serve immediately.

title: minestrone(low calorie soup)
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine all ingredients. Cover. Microwave on High 25 to 35 minutes or
until vegetables are tender, stirring once or twice.
Serves 6.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on floured cloth-covered board.
(Keep remaining dough chilled.)
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well together all the ingredients.
Put in 2 loaf pans that have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Each pan should be half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pepperoni appetizers
directions: Use a whisk to mix.
Add milk to flour.
Mix well until smooth.
Add egg, pepperoni and grated cheese.
Do not put too much pepperoni in each muffin as it will be too greasy.
Spoon mixture in muffin tins and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 36 muffins.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix these ingredients together and spoon into hot grease in skillet and fry until brown.

title: italian bread
directions: Mix dry yeast with warm water.
Add remainder of ingredients. Dough will be stiff.
Let rise once; punch down and let rise again.
Separate dough in half.
Roll out and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Use hand mixer to combine ingredients.	Sprinkle dried parsley on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: creamy fudge nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine. Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again. Mix sugar, flour and salt, then slowly pour in chocolate mixture. Add milk and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Mix in pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake for 50 minutes or until custard sets.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Cook the rice as directed on bag.
Drain and rinse with cold water and drain again.
Add to rice the sugar and stir in the dry jello.
Add the undrained fruit cocktail.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Chill.

title: stir-fry pork and veggies
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Stir-fry pork in 1 tablespoon oil, browning all sides. Remove pork and add remaining tablespoon of oil.
Add the next 5 ingredients and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add pork and cook all ingredients 2 more minutes.
Slowly add the set-aside mixture, stirring until sauce thickens and boils.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp-rice soup
directions: Simmer onion and pepper in large pan until tender.
Add undrained tomatoes, garlic, 1 1/2 cups water and both rice mix packets.
Bring to boil.
Add shrimp and return to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until rice is tender and shrimp are pink. Garnish with hot sauce.

title: sour cream cinnamon twists
directions: Bring sour cream to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in shortening, soda, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in egg and yeast.
Mix in flour.
Knead and cover with damp cloth.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with margarine, sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold in half, cut in 1-inch strips and twist.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: original toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Have ribs cut in serving size pieces.
Brown slowly in skillet.
Put in baking pan; pour off fat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion; cook until brown.
Add the next 9 ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Set oven at 350°.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scotch eggs
directions: This is a recipe that is wonderful for a brunch and the eggs can be prepared ahead of time and frozen.
Remove from freezer in time for sausage to thaw.
One to two eggs per person.

title: chicken enchiladas #1
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine; stir in cooked chicken and cream cheese.
Salt to taste.
Add cilantro.
Roll into tortillas.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Top with cheese. Pour in milk; cover.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Top with hot sauce and sour cream.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground beef; add chopped onion and chopped chilies.
Cook until onions are sauteed.
Line casserole with tortillas, bottom and sides.
Pour ground beef mixture over tortillas.
Layer this with strips of tortillas and grated Monterey Jack.
Continue layering until used up.
Mix mushroom soup and 1/2 can water and pour over casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese has melted and casserole has heated through.

title: easy espresso nog(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In the container of an electric blender, whirl yogurt, milk, espresso powder and vanilla until smooth, about 30 seconds. Pour into 6 or 8 small cups or glasses. Top with whipped cream and ground nutmeg, if desired.

title: raisin cake
directions: Bring washed raisins, water and shortening to a boil. Cover and boil 15 minutes or until moisture is gone. Let cool and add sugar, cold water, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and allspice. Add pinch of salt. Dissolve soda in boiling water. Add flour to make runny batter; add egg. Mix good and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown beef. Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry bacon or sausage and set aside.
Butter bread and place buttered side down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and add milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over bread.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle cheese over egg mixture and bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add sour cream and egg.

title: brenda's brownies
directions: Beat eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla until light.
Add flour and cocoa.
Stir until well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs; add salt and vanilla.
Mix until fluffy; pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Beat whipping cream until stiff; fold in pineapple and nuts.
Top pies and chill!

title: hobo pie
directions: Season ground beef as desired and lightly brown; drain grease. Add beans and picante sauce. Mix.
Put in medium baking dish. Top with cheese.
Put cornbread (mixed as if making cornbread) on top of cheese.
Bake until cornbread is done.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Mix the ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Melt 1 (12 ounce) package of semi-sweet chocolate chips and pour over cookies.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: pistachio fruit salad - light
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juices. In a bowl, whisk together reserved juice and pudding mix for 2 minutes. Mixture will be thick. Stir in the pineapple, fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges.

title: sea leg salad(crab salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cool and serve.
Experiment to discover amount needed of onion, celery, green pepper and pasta.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix
ham, pork, bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion, celery, salt and
pepper.
Pack	meat mixture firmly in loaf pan over pineapple slices.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix chili beans and seasoning mix together well.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Spread bean mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbling.
Put grated cheese on top and heat 5 to 8 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, rinse and drain.
Place in large bowl and sprinkle with seasoning.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Will keep for days in refrigerator.

title: baked crab salad
directions: Mix crab with celery and almonds.
Mix mayonnaise, minced onion, mushroom soup, Old Bay Seasoning, and lemon juice together and add to meat mixture.
Cover the top with Chinese noodles and bake for 25 min in a 375 degree oven.
It is important not to cook it too long because you just want to heat it, not to cook the celery.
The variation of the celery and nuts in contrast to the smoothness of the other ingredients is important.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Pour over margarine and mix slightly.
Heat sweetened fruit and pour over top.
Dough will rise over fruit.
Use rhubarb, apples, canned peaches or cherries. Bake at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Serves 12.

title: marinated round steak with mushrooms
directions: Combine mustard, chili sauce, lemon juice, Worcestershire, onion, paprika, salt and pepper.
Marinate defrosted steak in this sauce for 2 to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Saute sliced mushrooms in butter.
Drain steak and brown on both sides.
Add 1 cup water to sauce; pour over steak and mushrooms.
Cover closely and cook over very low heat for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Sift sugar, baking soda and flour together.
Add buttermilk to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add eggs, melted butter or margarine and coconut extract to mixture.
After mixing together, pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted Crisco, cocoa and salt.
Then add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar in 3 parts.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin, if needed, for good spreading to consistency.

title: chicken wings
directions: Lay in single layer in pan.
Pour dressing over and marinate. Turn wings occasionally.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until transparent.
Add rice and brown a little.
Add salt.
Add chicken broth.
Steam rice mixture in hot chicken broth for 25 or 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: edith harris' slaw
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup cold water over vegetables.
Soften gelatin with remaining 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt in a pan and bring to a boil.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Gradually beat in oil. Drain vegetables and mix lightly with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 10.

title: country bread pudding
directions: Blend sugar and butter in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add hot milk to egg mixture, mixing well.
Break and add bread until you reach desired consistency (usually 1/2 loaf).
Bake at 350° until pudding sets in center and golden brown around edge.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Using electric mixer, cream together butter, sugar and salt for 20 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour one cup at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let cool in pan, then turn out on cake rack.

title: quick quiche
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, milk, eggs and flour.
Add onion, cheese and ham.
Add bacon or bacon bits.
Mix all ingredients and pour into an 8-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot water banana chocolate cake!
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in eggs with mashed bananas. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Batter will be very thin.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan or 2 large loaf pans at 300° for about 50 minutes until done.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk. Pour batter into 11 x 15-inch pan, which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until cake pulls away from sides of pan. Frost with caramel frosting.

title: triple layer mud pie
directions: Mix chocolate and condensed milk until well blended. Pour into crust. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Rinse chicken with cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
In a small bowl, stir together oregano, basil, thyme and salt.
Use your fingers to loosen the skin from the tail to the neck.
Rub the herb mixture under the birds skin.
Brush chicken with oil or butter.

title: golden corn squares
directions: Combine eggs, corn, milk, onion and pepper; stir in rice, meat and cheese.
Turn into an ungreased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° until a knife inserted just off center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable sandwiches 2
directions: Blend together carrots, cucumber, onion, bell pepper and celery. Allow to drain well. Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt, blending well. Add to vegetables, stirring until well mixed.
Refrigerate to blend flavors at least overnight.
Makes about 10 sandwiches or 30 finger sandwiches.

title: korean chicken
directions: Flour wings and then deep fry.
Soak in sauce.
Serve.

title: jello salad
directions: Sift dry jello over cottage cheese and stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: chocolate dip
directions: In medium microwavable bowl stir corn syrup and cream. Microwave on High (100%) for 1 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Add chocolate; stir until completely melted.
Serve warm as a dip for fruit or cookies.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla and mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill for 4 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, cook garlic in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add bouillon and water to make broth.
Add tortellini.
Heat to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Add spinach and tomatoes.
Simmer for 10 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, butter and cream cheese until fluffy. Add sugar; mix until fluffy.
Add eggs alternately with flour, ending with flour.
Add the vanilla extract.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes to 35 minutes.
No peeping under any circumstances, as this cake will fall.
Cool and serve.

title: surprise pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: tofu lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as label directs and drain.
