In a medium bowl, mash tofu with fork; stir in Romano cheese, parsley, salt and egg. Arrange half of noodles, overlapping in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread half of tofu mixture on top of noodles, then top with half of zucchini, then half of Mozzarella, then half of spaghetti sauce.
Repeat for second layer.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes for easier serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans (two); cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water; blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake about 70 minutes.

title: mexican olive dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand 6 hours before serving.
(Keep chilled until serving.)
Good with corn chips.

title: big daddy casserole
directions: Saute ground round and onion together until meat is done; season to taste.
Don't overcook potatoes and macaroni; season to taste.
Layer in a pan, starting with a layer of potatoes, topped with a layer of meat, then a layer of cheese.
Layer macaroni, meat and cheese.
Top with tomatoes, crushing and squeezing juice evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly. Serve with a tossed salad and your favorite bread.

title: (busolao) holiday coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine; set aside.
Beat eggs and cream.
Add sugar and salt; beat until lemon colored and thick.
Add cooled margarine, then baking powder.
Add 2 cups of flour.
Add orange and lemon rinds and juices, flavorings, nuts, the remaining flour and raisins.

title: morning casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain it.
Grease bottom of dish, then line bottom with bread.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over bread.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard together. Pour over sausage, cheese and bread.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime mint salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O into undrained pineapple; mix well.
Add marshmallows and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add buttermints and Dream Whip (prepared).
Mix well.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan. To serve, thaw for about 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs, then stir in applesauce, then sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Then mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lo-cal pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, adding salt and 1 teaspoon oil to water.
Drain.
Pour cold water over noodles and drain again.
Place in bowl with a cover.
Pour the salad dressing over the noodles, mixing well.
Cover and chill.
Toss again before serving.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook beet juice, vinegar, sugar, salt and cornstarch until thickened.
Add beets and butter.

title: heavenly rice dessert
directions: Add sugar, pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and juice to cooked rice.
Mix lightly together; add the heavy whipped cream.

title: orzo salad
directions: Cook orzo according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; drain. Drain tomatoes, reserving 1 teaspoon oil. Chop 2 tablespoons tomato. Reserve remaining tomato for another use. Combine orzo, tomato, red pepper and next 3 ingredients in a bowl; toss gently. Combine reserved 1 teaspoon oil, vinegar and mustard; stir well with a wire whisk. Pour over orzo mixture; toss gently. Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Drain fruit. Save juice. Cook macaroni. Rinse. Drain. Mix eggs, sugar and flour with juice. Cook over medium heat until syrupy. Mix into macaroni and refrigerate overnight. Mix in Cool Whip and maraschino cherries.

title: lemon dessert sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine, in blender container.
Cover and blend at medium-high speed 30 seconds.
Pour into a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened. Stir in the margarine.
Add nutmeg, if used.
Serve warm over plain cakes or desserts.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: beet jelly
directions: Mix lemon juice, Sure-Jell and beet juice; cook to hard boil. Add sugar and Jell-O.
Boil 2 minutes or until jells.
Cool.
Put into jars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add garlic salt to taste also.
Add chicken to bowl and mix.
In greased baking dish layer Doritos, then spread mixture over and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty package of noodles into 6 cups of boiling water; boil rapidly for 7 to 10 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
Drain noodles.
Pour noodles into a glass baking dish.
Stir in the milk, egg and margarine or butter.
Slice cheese in pieces and spread evenly on noodles.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until top is brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: beefy mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomatoes and taco mix.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 can onions.
In a bowl, mix cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and eggs.
Place 3 tortillas on bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Overlap 6 tortillas around sides of dish.
Spoon meat mixture evenly in dish.
Top with 3 tortillas, then with cheese mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quicky pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 (9-inch) graham cracker crusts.
May use cherries for color.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Core head of cabbage to depth of 3 inches.
Cook to boiling. Remove leaves with tongs.
Let stand and cool.
Cut out hard center.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll mixture in cabbage leaves and cook with sauerkraut, remainder of cut up cabbage, spareribs, tomatoes (cut up) and tomato sauce.
Cook 4 to 6 hours on simmer.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Mix cream cheese (have it soft) and jello into the pineapple mixture until dissolved; set aside until partly set.
Whip Dream Whip and then mix all together.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain and clean salmon. Crumble well in large bowl. Add all ingredients. Mix well with hands and form into patties (thin). Place into hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot, low setting for several hours. Stir occasionally.

title: mary's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mini kolac rolls
directions: Mix cheese, flour and margarine together well.
Shape dough into small balls (about 1 1/4-inch); chill dough balls thoroughly. Roll out dough balls in 10x sugar; spread filling evenly on center of dough.
Roll up and seal or pinch ends.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes, or until just starting to brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Our favorite Solo fillings are blueberry, strawberry, poppy and pineapple.

title: chocolate mint cookies(jets)
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange julius - steve's way
directions: Squeeze fruit; remove seeds.
Put juice with pulp in blender. Add sugar, vanilla, protein powder and ice.
Blend on high.
Stop every now and then to stir.
Add 1/4 cup water, if needed.
Blend in slushy drink.
Pour into glasses and enjoy.

title: baked beans
directions: Empty half of beans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar and the mustard.
Sprinkle half over beans.
Top with the rest of the beans, again add the sugar mixture.
Top with bacon and catsup.
Bake, uncovered, in a slow oven (325°) for two and a half hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add graham cracker crumbs, then sprinkle the butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, coconut and chopped nuts on top.
Last, pour the Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: north georgia cornbread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
bake in a 400° oven about 15 minutes until
brown
and
firm.
Slice and serve with butter. This bread is good cooked in iron skillet.

title: quick brownie dessert
directions: Place brownie on individual plate.
Top each brownie with scoop or square of ice cream.
Spoon on cherry pie filling.
Top with whipped cream.
Nuts are optional.

title: white fudge cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each. Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Note:
To double, just double the ingredients.

title: grandma 'laynes cherry salad
directions: Combine pineapple, pie filling, nuts and milk in bowl.
Fold in topping.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Freeze overnight.
To serve, thaw for 1/2 hour to make cutting easier. Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, spices, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 1 Bundt pan or 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Split peppers and remove seeds.
Lay half of chilies on the bottom of a shallow dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with meat. Arrange rest of chilies over meat.
Add milk to flour, salt, pepper, eggs and hot pepper sauce.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Pour off fat; cool 5 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: triple fruit punch
directions: Combine frozen concentrates in punch bowl or pitcher.
Let stand to thaw partially, then stir until smooth and melted. Gradually stir in chilled water or ginger ale.
Add ice cubes and lemon slices.
Makes 20 punch servings (4 ounces each).

title: champion casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in margarine.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream and green onions with tops, thinly sliced.
Spoon noodles into a 2-quart greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cream cheese mixture.
Top with hamburger and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with tossed green salad and hot French bread.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs that you have dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove to racks to finish cooling.

title: chicken casserole\(makes big casserole; may be halved)
directions: Put noodles that have been cooked in salt water and drained into a large bowl.
Add mushroom soup, Durkee dressing, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, white pepper, salt, sour cream, chicken pieces and grated onion into mixture.
Stir this with a fork.
Add about 3 cups chicken stock to bowl.
Put into a casserole dish; sprinkle with grated bread crumbs which have been previously mixed with melted butter.
Cook at 400° until brown and bubbling.

title: aunt clara pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until smooth. Add 2 eggs at a time and mix. Add vanilla and Crisco.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with vegetables, chips or chunks of brown bread for dipping.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour over carrots.
Let stand overnight.
Serve cold.
Lasts for days!

title: easy microwave pralines
directions: Mix ingredients and cook in microwave for 20 minutes. Stir until it begins to get thick. Quickly spoon onto wax paper.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and grind.
Boil them 1 minute.
Set aside and skim.
Pour into small glasses.
Add red or green coloring.
Makes 6 cups.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Good for chicken, spareribs, etc.
Cook in casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350°.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Combine juice concentrate, fruit, milk, water and honey in a blender. Blend at high speed until thick and smooth, about 1 minute. Add ice cubes, one at a time, and blend until smooth and frothy. Garnish with a whole strawberry if you wish. Yield: 5 servings.

title: smooth n' creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding and milk in a small bowl.
Beat slowly with mixer about 1 minute, it should be thick, or beat a little longer. Fold in whipped (topping) Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Store in fridge.
Will frost one cake.
Keep in a cool place.

title: banana salad
directions: Combine and toss with favorite dressing.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Add to graham cracker crust and top with meringue.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until top is brown.
Chill and serve.

title: crunchy nut cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt; stir in and add nuts.
Shape level tablespoon into ball.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.

title: lemon pudding pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes. Bake in Bundt cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake about 40 minutes in a 350° oven or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool in pan about 10 minutes, then place cake on wire rack to cool completely.

title: smothered hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl (except shortening).
Make into patties and brown in skillet on both sides.
Remove from skillet and use drippings to make gravy.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to boil and cook to soft ball. Remove from heat; stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Spread in buttered dish to cool.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add milk; boil slowly for 3 minutes.
Cool. Add powdered sugar; beat until thick enough to spread.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside. Combine oil, eggs and sugar and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir well with beater for 1 minute. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Break lettuce, place
on
the
bottom
of the bowl.
Cut cauliflower and put it on top of the lettuce (the flower part). Cut the onion in
ringlets and place on top of the cauliflower. Mix the
Parmesan
cheese
with
the
mayonnaise.
Spread
this mixture on top of the vegetables with a spatula.
Crumble bacon on top of
mayonnaise and cheese mixture.
Put in refrigerator. Cover tightly for 8 hours.
When ready to serve, toss thoroughly.

title: zucchini and tomato with cheese
directions: Wash squash, cut off ends and any "ugly spots."
Slice squash 1/4-inch thick.
Dice onion.
Cut tomato in bite-size pieces. Steam (I use nonstick skillet) squash, onion and seasoning until tender.
Add tomato and cheese.
Serve when tomato is hot and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line dish with graham crackers.
Pour half of mixture of milk, pudding and Cool Whip over crackers.
Then, put another layer of crackers.
Pour rest of mixture over crackers and top with layer of crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored, add sugar gradually. Then add syrup, salt, and vanilla.
Mix well and add pecans. Pour into pastry pie shell and bake in oven 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed celery
directions: Mix the cheeses, onion and cream together.
Stuff celery. Chill and serve.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend butter and Cheddar cheese.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix by hand.
Put on cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Boil water in saucepan.
Mix other ingredients and add to water.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently on low heat (about 15 minutes).
Pour into loaf pan and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, cut into 1/2-inch slices and fry in butter until browned on both sides.
Serve with maple syrup for breakfast.

title: easy italian supper
directions: In large skillet, brown lean ground beef.
Add Pasta Accents and spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: sourdough hotcakes
directions: When making hotcakes from the starter taken from previous batch, mix starter, flour and water only using the same amount of flour and water (can add more for larger batch or less for small batch as it is not critical as to amounts) and about 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons sugar.
Next morning take out starter for next time before adding rest of ingredients.
Put a plate under the sourdough pot just in case it should get too active and run over the top; another MESS!

title: burritos
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Add 1/2 can of soup, 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup of picante sauce.
Mix well.
Take each flour tortilla and spread with refried beans.
Add 2 tablespoons of meat mixture, sprinkle with grated cheese and roll.
Place in baking dish.
Take remaining meat mixture, soup, beans and cheese and spread on top (beans 1st, then meat, soup, then cheese).
Cover tortillas well with mixture so they won't dry out.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or microwave on High for 16 minutes.
Rotate dish halfway through cooking time.

title: punch
directions: When ready to serve, add 2 quarts to 1/2 of the punch or 4 quarts to full recipe.
Serves 50 people.

title: chicken garden saute
directions: In skillet or electric frypan, brown chicken in oil.
Sprinkle with rosemary (or other herbs of your choice) and salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Cover and cook for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Uncover; cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, or until tomato liquid has thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: verna maes' texas brag
directions: Melt 1/2 stick melted butter in long baking dish.
Add cherry pie filling, pineapple and juice.
Layer this with cake mix.
On top, add coconut, pecans and 1 1/2 sticks melted butter.
Bake until brown at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot salad or copper pennies
directions: Wash and prepare vegetables.
Put carrots, onion and pepper in casserole dish.
In saucepan bring to a boil the sugar, oil, tomato soup and vinegar.
When mixture boils, pour over vegetables in the casserole dish.
Toss lightly and refrigerate.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown (about 10 minutes).
Let cool.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill evaporated milk.
Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Chill until partially set.
Whip Jell-O.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip the milk and add to Jell-O mixture.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix ingredients.
Pour in crusts and chill until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Carrots and celery may also be added.
I also just scrub the potatoes and carrots and shred them instead of peeling them.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease 11 x 7-inch casserole dish.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Put broccoli in casserole and top with chopped chicken.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese, then mix bread crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cholesterol-free chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: turkey with salsa mole poblano
directions: Brown the turkey thighs in a bit of oil in a very heavy skillet.
Place them in a kettle, barely covered with water.
Bring to a boil, cover and turn down the heat, and simmer for 40 minutes. Turn off the heat, cover the pot and leave the turkey in the broth for another 45 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Save money by mixing this recipe and store in airtight containers until needed, but no longer than 6 weeks.

title: mandarin slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, oranges, celery and green pepper.
Beat cream until stiff.
Add vinegar, slowly, salt and pepper.
Continue beating until well blended.
Mix with slaw ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: dick's dinner
directions: In a frying pan, melt butter.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Blend in soup and milk.
Combine in soup and milk.
Combine macaroni and soup mixture and remaining ingredients except chips.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with crushed chips. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cocktail pick-up chicken sticks
directions: Cut tips of wings and discard.
Divide each wing in half. Melt butter. Dip each wing in butter, then in flour mixture. Place on wax paper until all are coated.
Arrange in single layers. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: oriental slaw
directions: In skillet, brown Ramen noodles and almonds. Add soup packet just before removing from heat. Set aside. Mix soy sauce, sugar, oil and vinegar. Pour over slaw mix and let set. Stir in noodles just before serving.

title: hot dog macaroni and cheese delight
directions: Follow steps on box for cooking macaroni and cheese.
Slice hot dogs and stir into prepared macaroni and cheese.
Put in microwave for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.

title: uncooked peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add peanut butter, powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Mix well and shape in fingers or any shape.
Melt chips with wax over hot water in double boiler.
Dip cookies in chocolate mix.
Cool on wax paper.
These keep well for several days.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water; drain well.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Melt 3/4 stick of oleo or butter in frying pan.
Add stuffing mix; pack in a 2-quart dish.
Pour squash mixture over stuffing and sprinkle rest of stuffing mix on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip(preparation time: 15 minutes)
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with sour cream.
Chop medium onion and mix into mixture along with 2 packages of taco mix.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Over that spread a jar of taco sauce. Next, sprinkle over mixture the jalapeno or sweet peppers, depending on how hot you want it.
Spread lettuce over top of that.
Next, spread chopped tomato, then shredded Cheddar cheese over all.
Use taco chips to scoop out.

title: vic's grape gumball punch
directions: Blend coconut milk with 4 cans grape soda and ice. In a separate bowl, combine banana juice, orange juice, apple juice and strawberry syrup. Stir in blended mixture, adding 2 remaining cans of grape soda last. Finally, garnish with sliced oranges.

title: a.1. honey glaze(makes 1 cup)
directions: In small saucepan, over medium-high heat, heat all ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Use as glaze on ham during last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: easy potato casserole for brunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Top with corn flakes and melted butter to taste and return to oven for 10 more minutes.
Serve.
Recipe can be easily doubled.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes, cover with water and boil until just tender. Drain and chill.
Slice and cut into cubes.
Combine mayo, yogurt, dill weed and onion powder.
Add remaining ingredients to potatoes.
Pour dressing over potato mixture and toss.
Yields 8 servings.

title: saltless salt
directions: Grind together and place in salt shaker.

title: frozen pineapple pie
directions: Slightly drain pineapple and mix together pineapple, Eagle Brand, nuts and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into the two pie shells and freeze. Thaw 8 minutes before serving.
Pies can be kept in freezer for months.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: In a large saucepan, cook zucchini in boiling salted water until tender, about 5 minutes; drain.
In medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and saute until onion is tender; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir onion-bacon mixture into drained zucchini; add remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Serve piping hot. Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, water, lard and raisins. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir into cooled raisin mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until cake tests done with a wooden pick.
Yields 16 servings.

title: sausage potato skillet dinner
directions: In large skillet, put enough oil to cover bottom.
Add potatoes, turn to keep from sticking. Cook until potatoes are coated in oil.
Add onion and desired amount of sausage. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 c. water. Cover, reduce heat and cook slowly until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: hot onion dip(warm; not spicy)
directions: Mix all together in small casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Place into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumb topping.
Bake at 370° about 35 minutes.

title: sausage vegetable soup
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven cook sausage, celery, onion and garlic until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients except rotini and zucchini.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add rotini and zucchini.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rotini is tender.
Makes 6 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with 3/4 of package of dressing mix. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top of mix. Mix together the 2 cans of soups with the 2 cups of broth.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle remainder of dressing mix over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, yeast and salt; mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk, water, honey and shortening until warm.
Add to flour mixture.
Add egg; blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining all-purpose flour to make firm dough.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, 1 hour.
Divide into 2 parts and form into loaves.
Put into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Let rise again until double, about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Spread butter over top of each loaf.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all together with mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour into buttered Bundt pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ranch style deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks and set egg whites aside.
In small bowl, mash yolks with fork.
Add mayonnaise, salad dressing and mustards; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Evenly fill the whites.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.

title: ann marie's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine sifted and liquid ingredients with a few swift stokes. Beat in 2 Tbsp. melted margarine.

title: cherry fluff square
directions: Crush crackers and mix all together.
Save 1/2 cup for top. Mix rest and press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt 32 large marshmallows and 1/2 cup milk.
Cool and let set.
Fold in 1 cup of whipped cream.
Spread 1/2 of this on top of crumbs and cool. Spread cooled cherry pie filling on top.
Then spoon the rest of marshmallow mixture on top of cherries.
Add remaining crumbs. Chill.

title: salisbury steak and gravy
directions: Brown (fast) pork chops.
Cook sliced potatoes almost done. Place meat in bottom of baking dish or pan; sprinkle with garlic salt.
Put potatoes on top of meat; cover with a can of mushroom soup.
Bake at low heat until brown.
Salt potatoes to taste.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms and hollow out.
Chop enough pieces to make 3 tablespoons.
Cook pieces with onions in oil.
Stir in salami, cheese spread and catsup.
Stuff into mushroom crowns.
Sprinkle with soft, fine bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, stir through to mix with mayonnaise.
Place in serving dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 6.

title: oriental chicken breasts
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan. Add chicken breast strips and marinate 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into a loaf.
Glaze top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 shallow dish unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: relish for meats
directions: Mix kraut and sugar; let stand overnight.
Chop celery, bell pepper and onions together.
Coarsely grate the carrots and chop the pimento.
Mix all ingredients together and put in covered jars.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: orange frozen salad
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Add the Cool Whip and oranges.
Pour into a small oblong dish.
Freeze.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in morsels.
Pat down half of mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving other half for top.

title: funny face pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray; set aside. Remove dough from package. DO NOT UNROLL DOUGH. Slice dough into 4 equal pieces. Knead each piece of dough until ball forms. Pat or roll out each ball into 4-inch disk. Place disks on prepared baking sheet. Spread 1/4 cup sauce on each disk. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Decorate with toppings to create faces. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese to resemble hair. Bake 10 minutes or until cheese is just melted and bottoms of pizzas are light brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar and butter in a large mixing bowl.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix together and stir in oats.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press cookie ball with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together dry milk, sugars, water, oil and egg.
Add vanilla.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in zucchini, nuts and cherries.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken in foil at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Grease a 9 x 5-inch casserole.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix together with the mayonnaise, soup, curry powder and lemon juice. In casserole, put layers of chicken chunks, broccoli, mayonnaise mixture and dressing; mix with melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shake and bake potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes with skins on and cut into wedge.
Place potato wedges in bowl of cold water.
Pour Shake 'n Bake into plastic bag and put potatoes a few at a time in bag to coat good.
Place well coated potatoes in large casserole dish and put pats of butter on top of potatoes.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: microwave butter crumb potatoes
directions: Roll potatoes in butter, then in bread crumbs.
Arrange potatoes in baking dish; drizzle with remaining butter.
Heat 10 to 12 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Let stand, covered, 4 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil cut up chicken until tender. Cool. (Save wings and back, all boney parts, for soup.) Take chicken off bone. (Throw away or save for another use all skin and bones.) In a clean pot, measure 5 1/3 cups of broth that chicken was cooked in. Chop green pepper and onion and add to broth. Add 2 teaspoons of salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper. Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes. Add 2 cups rice. Cover and simmer for approximately 45 minutes or until rice is soft and liquid is absorbed. Turn burner off and allow to sit covered 20 minutes.

title: christmas fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and mix with fruit.
Add eggs to creamed mixture. Add flour-fruit mixture alternately with next 5 ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Pour into pans lined with greased paper. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Cover cakes with greased paper.
Steam for 2 hours, then bake in slow oven 300° 1 1/2 to 2 hours, removing paper last 1/2 hour to dry surface.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt all ingredients in saucepan on low to medium heat until smooth and creamy.
Serve hot with chips.

title: dateballs
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and dates in saucepan.
Heat on medium heat until mixture pulls away from pan.
Add nuts and vanilla; cook 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Make in balls and roll in coconut.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Drain pineapple; boil zucchini 25 minutes, stirring often. Gets mushy but don't add liquid. Add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice. Cook 15 minutes. Add Jell-O. Cook another 15 minutes. Put in jars and seal. Makes 5 pints.

title: chile corn casserole
directions: Mix together well and bake in greased shallow pan about 30 minutes or until set with oven around 325° to 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix 4 cups milk and pudding. Add Cool Whip and beat thoroughly. Layer with graham crackers in a 13 x 9-inch pan, using crackers, 1/2 pudding, crackers, 1/2 pudding and topping with crackers. Chill while making topping.

title: dried peach custard pie
directions: Cook peaches as directed on package; drain and mash.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar.
Cool; spread in pie shell and set aside.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour and butter; mix well.
Beat in egg yolks, milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: old fashioned gingery cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add rest and mix.
Make small balls (about 1 teaspoon batter).
Roll in extra sugar, place on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 2 or 3 drops of water on top of each.
They will flatten out and crackle.

title: cookies for ms billie
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10-12 minutes.
About 4 dozen cookies.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop onto hot griddle.
Brown on both sides; serve warm.

title: easy millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; fold in 1 large container Cool Whip topping.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: good shortcake biscuits
directions: Put dry ingredients and Crisco in bowl and work until small particles form.
Add eggs to milk and work in with fork (not too much).
Roll out 1 inch thick.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or more.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle lots of powdered sugar while still warm.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: german style oven pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs with fork.
Slowly blend in flour. Stir in salt and softened butter.
Add milk and blend.
Batter may be slightly lumpy.
Grease 10-inch ovenproof skillet or 3-quart round baking dish.
Pour batter into cold skillet or dish.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 7 minutes more.
Do not open oven door while baking.
Serve immediately with melted butter, powdered sugar and lemon wedges.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.
(Can also be served with warm applesauce.)

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast into warm water and add salt, sugar and shortening.
Start adding flour until it's not sticky.
Knead dough for 5 minutes.
Next, butter bottom of bowl and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Knead dough again and let rise 1/2 hour.
Shape biscuits at least 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
18 to 24 biscuits.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture; beat.
Dredge berries in 1 cup flour and fold into creamed mixture.
Pour into tube pan, which has been buttered and coated with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zesty goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Cook macaroni in medium size saucepan until done.
Drain and rinse macaroni.
Place back in saucepan and add ground beef, stewed tomatoes, catsup, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
If too thick, add a little water.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix eggs, flour, salt, sugar, soda and fruit cocktail (including juice) and put into large baking pan.
Do not grease pan.
Before baking, sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over batter. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: diet corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix corn meal and flour.
Add salad dressing, buttermilk and egg.
If needed, add water to make mixture.
Pour into sprayed skillet.
Bake in 400° oven until brown and test for doneness.

title: philadelphia cheese ball
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients in electric mixer.
Fold in dried beef, diced fine.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Make into balls.
Bake on ungreased cooking sheet at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: magic eye of round
directions: Cover all sides and ends of the roast with brown mustard (use entire jar). Roll roast in salt, covering meat completely (there should be no mustard visible). Place roast on a rack in roasting pan. Bake at 475° to 500° 10 to 12 minutes/pound for rare, 12 to 15 minutes/pound for medium and 15 to 20 minutes/pound for well done.

title: cold day chili(four servings)
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain.
Add beans, tomatoes, water, chili powder, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until heated through.
Serve.

title: shrimp soup dip
directions: Place all but shrimp in blender.
Process until smooth.
Add shrimp and blend until shrimp are chopped into small bits.

title: raspberry chicken
directions: In a large, heavy bottomed frying pan, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes on each side.
Add the shallots.
Turn heat down and cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Transfer chicken to a platter.
Pour raspberry vinegar and jam into the frying pan; bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes.
Turn heat down; stir in the tomato paste, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Simmer until sauce thickens slightly. Spoon in 2 tablespoons butter.
Return chicken to sauce on low; cook for 10 minutes.
Serve with fresh raspberries and chopped chives, sprinkled on top.
Serves 6.

title: baked sausage
directions: Brown sausage and drain real good on paper towels.
Cut in 1 1/2 to 2-inch
pieces.
Put
in baking pan and mix onions and peppers and add
a	little	sugar
and
salt
and mix with tomato sauce and pour over sausage.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: great grandmother's corn bread
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with maple syrup.

title: chocolate roulage
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until thick and light.
Add vanilla, salt and cocoa; stir well.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Gradually fold into the chocolate mixture.
Pour into oblong (cookie sheet) pan with sides lined with wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto damp towel until cool; peel off wax paper and trim crusty edges. Spread with sweetened whipped cream.
Roll up and refrigerate, using towel to help roll.

title: hot artichoke cheese dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Spread evenly over bottom of well-greased shallow 2-quart baking dish. Scatter chilies on top.
Carefully spread mayonnaise over all.
Top with cheese.
Heat in 350° oven, covered, until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot with chips.

title: super cookie
directions: Cream together softened butter, sugars and eggs; add salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat well. Gradually add flour.
Stir in oats and corn flakes.
Add candies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cool and pull off bone and put in casserole dish.
Heat soups and milk; pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with chicken broth and spoon over chicken and soups. Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add salt, coconut and nuts.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 minutes at 275°.
Store in airtight container (after cooling) about 5 days before serving.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate before serving with vegetables.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush anchovies to a paste. Add eggs and beat until liquid. Add pepper, olive oil (discard garlic cloves first), vinegar and lemon juice. Beat with fork until blended.
Entire process may be done in blender.
Cut romaine into pieces 1/2-inch long.
Mix with dressing until coated. Add croutons and cheese.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs, flour, sugar, salt and milk together.
Stir in corn and pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: garlic steak sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and whip until fluffy.

title: pumpkin cheese roll
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute at high speed.
Add 1 cup sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold into sifted flour, soda, salt and spices. Bake in oiled jelly roll pan or oblong cookie sheet pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on powdered sugar dusted towel.
Roll up in towel and let cake cool.

title: chocolate cream drops
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Blend in melted chocolate.	Add sour cream and vanilla; mix well. Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Chill. Drop
rounded teaspoonfuls
on
lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at
for 8	to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Frost cooled cookies.

title: microwave sweet potato chips(an easy to make, lower fat alternative to potato chips.)
directions: In microwave dish, spread out sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle with water.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Mix in butter and brown sugar.
Microwave another 2 to 3 minutes.
Let sit.

title: texas chili
directions: Saute onions in very large skillet until transparent looking. Add meat.
Cook and stir until it loses its red color.
Add all of the other ingredients, except kidney beans.
Stir well.
Bring to boil, then cook at very low temperature for 4 hours.
Add kidney beans and cook about 20 minutes more.

title: pear cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla, baking soda and water.
Beat in flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg until creamy.
Fold in pears and walnuts.
Spray tube pan with Pam and spread batter evenly.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar in small bowl.
Shred cabbage in large bowl.
Add small bowl mixture to cabbage.
Chill before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center.
Add liquid mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Pour into well greased pans.
Bake at 350°.
Recipe makes six 6 x 3 x 2-inch pans; bake 40 minutes.
Or makes three 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans; bake 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes or longer before removing from pans.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk, vanilla and butter; boil until thick.
Pour in cooked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Mix ingredients and pour dressing over mixture.
Toss and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Combine noodles, tuna and soup.
Add a can of water.
Place in a baking dish.
Crush potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mini chocolate cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Lightly grease (2 1/2 or 2 3/4-inch) muffin pan cups; set aside.

Combine cream cheese and sugar in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes, scraping side of bowl 1 or 2 times. Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well blended, about 2 minutes.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, eggs, instant pudding mix, mild and oil in a large mixing bow. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Evenly divide batter between 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Cool, then cut each layer in half horizontally, so that there are 4 thin layers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pastina and drain.
Over low heat, cook juice from fruit, sugar and flour.
Stir frequently.
When sauce is clear and thickened, add beaten eggs and margarine.
Pour sauce over pastina and refrigerate overnight.
Fold in fruit, cherries, and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: fruit surprise
directions: Pour fruit in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit, drizzle melted butter on top of cake mix.
Put pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie crust is golden brown, about 35 minutes.

title: apple chutney
directions: In heavy 4 to 5-quart pot, combine apples, onions, raisins, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, pickling spice, ginger and cayenne pepper.

Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, then reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered for about 2 hours, or until most of the liquid has cooked away and the mixture is thick enough to hold its shape in a spoon.
Stir often to prevent the chutney from sticking.
Remove from heat and ladle into hot sterilized jars.
Makes 3 pints.

title: beef, cabbage and tomato casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in vegetable oil in large skillet.
Add tomatoes and salt; bring to a boil.
In casserole, layer cabbage and meat mixture, beginning and ending with cabbage. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° (shredded cheese may be added to top for last 3 to 5 minutes, if desired).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and boil until tender. Drain well and add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 450° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 minutes.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
The pie filling makes the dressing for it.
Very good.
You can add pecans, coconut or almonds if you prefer.
Serves approximately 15.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together wafer crumbs, 1/2 stick butter, 1/2 stick oleo and white sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Set aside.
Beat with mixer, eggs, 1 stick butter, 1 stick of oleo and powdered sugar.
Beat 15 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Add a layer of sliced bananas, a layer of pineapple and Cool Whip.
Garnish top with pecans and cherries.
Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: peanut blossoms(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Mix together first three ingredients in small bowl.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients. Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a solid milk chocolate candy Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that the cookie cracks around the edges.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: italian hamburg
directions: Put hot water in heavy skillet which has close fitting lid and bring to a boil.
Add ground meat.
Cook until meat turns gray, stirring often.
Sprinkle over meat the chopped onion, uncooked spaghetti, salt and parsley.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Do not mix! Place close fitting lid on skillet and turn flame very low.
Let it cook slowly, without lifting lid, for 30 minutes.
Remove lid; stir well.
Sprinkle cheese over top and serve at once.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crusts.
Pour into crusts.
Chill 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until crumbly, then add water. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie crust.

title: c.k.'s taos fruit salad
directions: Cut fruit to bite-size pieces and mix all together; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Mix in the vanilla yogurt and the vanilla extract. Chill slightly before serving.

title: black magic chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Add next 2 and mix well. Next, add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Bake in greased tube pan at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry tarts
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into a bowl.
Cut butter in with dry ingredients.
Mix and mash until well mixed and crumbly.
Add beaten egg and milk together.
Mix with other ingredients thoroughly.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Make small balls about 2-inches big.
Put them on the cookie sheet and flatten to 1/8-inch thick (should be about 4 to 5 inches in diameter).
Drop 1 tablespoon jam on half the circle.
Fold over other half to make a pocket.
Crimp edges with a fork.
Cook at 350° in a preheated oven for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes about 10 tarts.

title: holiday eggnog for the whole family
directions: In a saucepan,	combine
all
ingredients and heat over low burner stirring constantly.
May also be served cold.

title: no bake date cookies
directions: Cool.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Serves 50.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased and floured Pyrex 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and shortening in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Serve with apple slices.

title: beef casserole italiano
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion together.
Then add tomato sauce, parsley, oregano and basil to ground beef mixture and simmer for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine spinach and Ricotta cheese.
Spoon spinach mixture around edge of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon meat mixture in center.
Arrange the cheese over meat.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in Italian dressing for several hours.
While noodles are cooking, grill chicken breasts on outdoor grill.
Add the remaining ingredients to the fettuccine noodles.
Cut cooked chicken breasts into bite size pieces and stir into fettuccine noodles and remaining ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas (blend to liquid), then add flour and soda (mixed).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for about 55 minutes.
May be baked in two loaf pans, 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch or a tube pan.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook grits in water until thick.
Stir in everything except eggs.
Add eggs when cool.
Put in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice eggplants about 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Soak in salted water 20 minutes and drain.
Cover with boiling water and drain immediately.
Pat eggplants dry. Melt butter in a frying pan and saute eggplants 2 minutes on each side.
Place one layer in a buttered baking dish; top with half of the cheese and sprinkle with pepper.
Repeat the layers once more. Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sugarless sugar cookies
directions: Beat oil, margarine and sugar substitute together.
Add the milk, egg and vanilla and beat well. Sift together the salt, baking powder and flour and blend in.
Drop by teaspoonfuls at least 3 inches apart on nonstick cookie sheets and bake in oven at 375° for 7 minutes.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: curried chicken
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan and curry powder until transparent.
Add soup and cream.
Heat, without boiling. Sprinkle breasts with salt and paprika.
Arrange in buttered baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Cover dish and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup.
Form into a loaf.
Cover bottom of pan with ketchup (about 1/2-inch deep).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dairy fruit salad
directions: Cream cheese until smooth. Add powdered sugar and Miracle Whip. In a large mixing bowl, put the drained fruit, Cool Whip, cream cheese mixture and marshmallows. Stir together and chill overnight.

title: shake-'em-up scrambled eggs
directions: Place eggs, cheese, salt and pepper in a covered jar and shake well.
Heat butter in skillet until melted over medium heat.
Be sure skillet is coated with butter.
Pour egg mixture into hot skillet and cook over medium heat without stirring.
Turn gently with pancake turner when eggs on the bottom start to get firm. Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until eggs are slightly firm.

title: fuzzy navels
directions: Wash fresh unpeeled peach (stone removed).
Put all ingredients in blender and let her rip!

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, stir first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: fried rattlesnake
directions: After cleaning and skinning the snake, section into 4-inch pieces.
Coat with corn meal and flour.
Deep fry as you would fish.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding using the 3 cups milk. When thickened, fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with whole graham crackers.
Pour half of the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Place another layer of whole crackers over this.
Add remaining pudding and another layer of graham crackers.
Carefully ice top of graham crackers with frosting. Refrigerate overnight. Serves 20 to 24.

title: raw peanut candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until threads.
Add peanuts and cook until peanuts stop popping.
Add soda and beat.
Pour in greased plates.

title: coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and brown sugar.
Add eggs, oil, salt, soda and coffee.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baker's sheet.
Top with chips and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: baked chocolate cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine butter, crumbs and sugar; pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Add milk; blend until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool to room temperature, then chill.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar together.
Add milk.
Melt butter in baking pan (2 x 8 x 13-inch).
Pour batter in buttered baking pan without stirring butter into batter.
Pour peaches and syrup on top of batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Form into a ball with hands.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin pie spice, eggs and milk.
Blend well. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top, then drizzle butter on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Chill. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine, cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Cool and add to potato salad.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all fruit.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Serve over fruit.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Wash and shred cabbage.
Add onion, salt, sugar and pepper. Stir in mayo or dressing, mixing as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix together with mixer for 3 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 layers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour melted butter on top.
Add peaches and juice.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour the second three ingredients over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until top is golden.

title: farm bean salad
directions: Place these in a colander and drain well, then place in large bowl.
Add dressing. Mix well and serve.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Cream together the Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Stir in dry jello and mix well.
Fold in oranges, pineapple and coconut.
Pour in flat baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
May use strawberry or blueberry jello.

title: kyle's cookies
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.	Add vanilla and eggs. Add soda, salt, flour and oatmeal.	In double boiler, melt milk chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk, 3 tablespoons butter and vanilla.
Place 2/3 of batter into 10 x 15 greased and floured pan.
Pour chocolate mixture in double boiler over cookie dough in the 10 x 15 pan and top with remaining 1/3 batter.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut-sour cream cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat 2 minutes on high speed. Reduce speed to low; beat 1 minute.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: hungarian pork paprika
directions: Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Toss with meat.
In skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Stir in tomatoes.
Cook uncovered over medium heat 20 minutes or until meat is tender, stirring often.
Remove pan from heat.
Remove 1/2 cup of sauce mixture from skillet and blend with sour cream.
Return to skillet.
Blend well.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: snow ghost cocoa cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir into milk and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Carefully press plastic wrap directly on pie filling.
Cool; chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip or meringue.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown raw rice in 2 tablespoons of oil where chicken has been fried, crumbs and all.
Add bell peppers and onion.
Saute.
Add water or chicken broth and cook on medium heat until rice is done.

title: squash pie
directions: Boil squash in water slightly salted until tender.
Drain water; add butter and seasonings and mashed squash with other ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter.
Spread all over a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread vanilla wafer crumbs on top of butter.
Spread chocolate chips on top of crumbs.
Spread butterscotch chips on top of chocolate chips.
Spread coconut flakes on top of butterscotch chips. Spread pecan pieces on top of coconut flakes.
Pour condensed milk over top and bake 25 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: wanda's christmas caramels
directions: Mix the Karo syrup and butter in a pan; bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In separate bowl, mix flour, sugar and Eagle Brand milk.
Place pan back on medium heat.
Slowly pour Eagle Brand mixture into the pan, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; cook, stirring constantly, approximately 45 minutes until mixture forms a fairly hard ball in cold water.
Remove from
heat.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour in buttered 1 inch deep pans.
Cool; cut into squares.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender with 1 medium onion, 2 sticks celery, salt and pepper; cool.
Skin and debone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Spread chicken in bottom of 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush Doritos and spread over chicken.
Next, spread onions and olives and add to soup.
Pour over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand for 10 minutes. Cream together both sugars, margarine and eggs. Add oatmeal mixture and mix well.

title: los angeles charbroiled steak
directions: Spread butter over steak.
Season with oregano, salt and pepper to desired taste.
Cook at 400° to 450° in oven until it is to your taste, medium or well done.
Serve with whatever side dishes you would like.

title: crescent sandwiches
directions: Open and break apart at perforation.
Press middle seam together to form rectangles.
Spread 1/2 mixture on each crescent section.
Roll up lengthwise and slice into 10 pieces.
Place 1/2 olive in center of each pinwheel.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 18 minutes.
These can be made up to 2 hours ahead of baking time before baking.
Makes 20 sandwiches.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Slice cherries in half.
Mix with all ingredients; stir well. (Do not add water to jello.)
Chill overnight or several hours until stiff.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Layer in dish the tortillas, chilies, onion, chicken and cheese.
Mix chicken soup with chicken broth.
Pour over layers. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: kim's chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, broth, soup, onion and Veg-All in casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Mix milk and flour and pour over top; bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and oleo and spread in oblong pan.
Beat egg whites stiff; add powdered sugar.
Add cream cheese (softened) and lemon juice.
Spread on first mixture.
Slice bananas on top of this. Drain crushed pineapple and spread on top of bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on this.
Sprinkle chopped up pecans on this.
Cut cherries in half and put on top.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Break bread in small pieces. Brown sausage and drain fat.
Mix all ingredients well; put in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. This may be made in the evening, refrigerated overnight and baked the next morning. Serves 8.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Placed butter in cream in heavy skillet and cook until butter is melted and bubbles. Stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg; remove from heat and stir in cheese. Reheat if necessary. Pour over fettuccine in pot; toss with 2 forks over low heat 2 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley. Serves 4.

title: potato pudding
directions: Mix last 3 items. Crumble over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Then uncover and cook, uncovered, until brown.

title: iced jello
directions: Mix and chill until firm.
Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: nutty fruit salad
directions: In a medium sized bowl, combine the bananas, apples, pineapple, cherry halves and peanuts.
Mix in enough mayonnaise to generously coat all the fruit and nuts.

title: cheesy meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese and put in 1-1/2 quart baking dish.
Press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and sprinkle top with grated Cheddar cheese. Return to oven for 5-10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: neene peg's enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion with salt, pepper and garlic. Place 1 or 2 slices American cheese on flour tortilla shell with large spoonful of meat mixture.
Roll up and place in baking dish. Mix enchilada sauce, taco sauce and chile together and spread over enchiladas.
Cover with grated American cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Also good served with white cheese dip.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for butter and Ritz crackers.
Melt one stick butter and crumble up one stack Ritz crackers.
Mix with the butter.
Spread over vegetable mixture in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Sift meal 3 times and mix with boiling water.
Stir until smooth and free of lumps.
Add salt, shortening, milk and beaten egg yolks.
Beat whites until stiff; fold in.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm in baking dish.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in extra sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: white trash candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon on to foil.
Let cool.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales with a vegetable peeler or knife, if desired.
Place asparagus in a vegetable steamer over boiling water; cover and steam 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Arrange asparagus in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: pizza crust
directions: Cut together flour, salt and butter.
Stir in yeast and knead.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs, salt, flour, vanilla, baking powder and milk.
Now add raisins, pecans, red cherries, pineapple, Brazil nuts and dates.
Grease and lightly flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: monkey bread
directions: After removing biscuits from can, cut each into 4 pieces. Using approximately 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon, mix thoroughly.
Coat each piece and put in a loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
With remaining sugar and cinnamon, add about 1 tablespoon of melted butter.
Mix well and spoon over top of loaf.
Don't overdo the top or bread may come out too sticky on bottom.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes for small loaf or 35 minutes for large loaf.

title: taco dish
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions, sauce, soup and milk.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer meat with cheese and chips, topping with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix butter and spices together and rub all over chicken, inside and out.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: indian cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients, then add pineapple.
Pour into an ungreased pan.
Cover with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and blend together.
Grease pan well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Mix flour and baking soda together.
Add flour alternately with milk to sugar and shortening mixture.
Beat egg whites with 1/3 cup sugar; fold into batter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dip
directions: Mash the cream cheese together, cut the end of green onion and mix the cut up meat.
Serve as dip.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together ingredients and put into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Baste with syrup and bake for another hour and 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes in ungreased loaf pan.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake in well greased tube pan, filling half full.
Bake remainder of batter in greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° as you would regular cornbread.

title: barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Place each biscuit in greased muffin cup, pressing dough to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon meat mixture into each cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Loosen with spatula; remove from pans.
Makes 10.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in lemon. Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill. Serve with deli-style crackers.

title: bird nests
directions: Melt peanut butter.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
(This step can also be done in the microwave oven.)
Stir in chow mein noodles. On wax paper, drop spoonfuls of mixture. Press spoon into center to form bird nests.
Drop 2 or 3 colored candies in the center to look like eggs.
Let cool and enjoy.
Can be frozen.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well. Pour into pitcher or punch bowl. Serve punch over ice and garnish with cherries.

title: turkey hobo
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well with mayonnaise.
Stuff each hot dog bun with half of the mixture.
Wrap each hobo in foil.
Heat in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chinese new year's cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Mix in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Chill in freezer 15 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator in covered can as long as you want.

title: easy taco casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown ground beef; drain.
Add salsa, mayonnaise, and chili powder, mix.
In an ungreased 2 qt. baking dish, layer half of the meat mixture, chips and cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350 degrees uncovered 20-25 minutes or until heated through.
Just before serving top with
lettuce and tomatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and Cool Whip.
If desired, add chopped walnuts. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart oblong Pyrex dish.
Cover and freeze. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
Serves 12.

title: patriotic birthday "little logs"
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in paper baking cups as directed on package.
Cool.
Remove paper baking cups.
Put two cupcakes together end to end with frosting to form logs.
Frost sides, leaving ends of logs (tops of cupcakes) unfrosted.
With tines of fork, make lines in frosting to resemble bark.
Decorate each log with a hatchet cut from construction paper.
Makes 12 to 15 logs.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and put into pie shell.
Bake at 250°
for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's hot water cornbread
directions: Notes:
The sugar helps the pones to brown and improves flavor.
One cup yellow meal and 1 cup white meal is best.
Use a medium size mixing bowl.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread onto the crust that has cooled.
Next, pour boiling water over jello until dissolved and then add the strawberries.
Cool slightly, pour over other layers and refrigerate.

title: white salad
directions: Whip Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Cream together the cheese and mayonnaise.
Add
marshmallows and drained fruit.
Fold in Dream Whip and garnish with red or green maraschino cherries.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare red jello as per directions.
Pour into rectangular baking dish and let set.
(I use a glass dish.)
Cook milk with marshmallows until they are melted.
Add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon jello (dry powder) and stir well. Remove from heat and add undrained crushed pineapple.
Let set until cool.
Blend in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Pour over set red jello; let set.
Prepare green jello as per directions.
Pour over white layer and let set.
Cut and serve as desired.

title: hot percolator punch
directions: Combine brown sugar, juices and water in a percolator.
Insert basket with cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Plug in and perk.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 low calorie muffins.

title: mediterranean phyllo turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in a large nonreactive mixing bowl.
Add pine nuts, peppers, Feta cheese, parsley, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir to combine, cover and refrigerate while you prepare phyllo.

title: quesadilla
directions: Spread green chilies and cheese in casserole dish, sprayed with Pam. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over cheese and chilies. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Melt butter in thick boiler.
Add flour and stir until flour is dissolved.
Add chicken broth.
(If gravy seems too thick, add a little water.)
Add salt and pepper.
After gravy thickens, add eggs and turkey or chicken.

title: termater puddin'
directions: Place 1/3 of bread cubes in bottom of a well-buttered baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Do this until all the bread is used.
Heat the rest of the ingredients.
Boil.
Pour over the bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Cook on low in crock-pot.

title: crabby's
directions: Cut each 1/2 of muffin into quarters.
Place on cookie sheets and broil lightly on each side until semi-crisp.
(This prevents them from being soggy when cooked later.)
Mix remaining ingredients and spread generously on top of each quarter.
Place back on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store, frozen, in tin or Ziploc bag until ready to use.

title: georgie porgie
directions: Mix and pat in a baking pan the flour, butter or margarine and chopped nuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: brown chocolate icing
directions: Heat together first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Spread over cake.

title: chocolate pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add milk and sugar. Beat again.
Add flour and cocoa.
Stir in and mix well.
Add melted butter and stir in.
Fry on buttered griddle.
Roll or stack, covering with powdered sugar.
Yields 14 to 16 small pancakes.

title: onion soup
directions: Fry onions in butter over medium heat, covering to retain moisture, until tender.
Add water, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon cubes.
Simmer, covered, for approximately 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles(patrick's favorite cookie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by teaspoon into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll cookie dough in this mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately and cool.

title: kima from india
directions: In saucepan, cook beef and onion.
Stir in seasonings, potatoes, tomatoes, peas and water.
Cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Should be moist, but not soupy.
Serve on rice.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, softened butter, egg, water and vanilla together.
Pour in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, egg and Crisco. Add dry ingredients. Add milk alternately; add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Dice and boil potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and put into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let simmer about 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: rocky mountain chili
directions: Mix all together. Cook for 4 hours.

title: bran-oat bran muffins
directions: In a small bowl, pour boiling water over the Bran Buds. Cool. In a medium bowl combine the flour, soda, and salt. Blend white and brown sugar in a large bowl. Mix in canola oil by hand. Add beaten eggs and buttermilk. Stir by hand until smooth. BEAT in the Bran Buds mixture. By hand, stir in the flour mixture only until blended. Stir in the Common Sense Oat Bran by hand until well blended but not crushed. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: smoked salmon pate
directions: Mix all together and, if needed, thin with lemon juice or margarine.
Make into desired mold and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: chili mac
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Season to taste. Serves 4 to 6.

title: *florida chicken
directions: Combine flour, orange peel, paprika and 1 teaspoon of the salt and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Save 3 tablespoons flour mixture. Heat shortening in skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for about 40 minutes; turn occasionally. Add water, if necessary.
Remove chicken.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons drippings.
Add saved flour and blend well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add gradually, stirring constantly. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Pour over the chicken.
Good served on platter alone or over rice.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: kielbasa vegetable scallop
directions: In 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, mix potatoes, sauce mix, water, oleo and milk.
Stir in onions; place
sausage
on top. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 to 35
minutes
until potatoes are fork-tender.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.

title: special dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pan; pour one can chicken broth and butter over mixture.
Stir well.
Add salt, pepper and sage to taste.
