Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon, then mix together eggs, water, vanilla and butter; put aside.
Peel and core apples.
Cut up the apples in slices.
Grease a cake pan well.
Pour in the cake mixture, then arrange the apple slices in a circle from center to the outside of pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Crumble candy bars.
Set aside.
Pinch half of the cake in small pieces.
Put in bottom of a large dish.
Mix oleo, yolks and sugar.
Fold Cool Whip into sugar mixture.
Spread half of this mixture over the cake. Sprinkle half of the crumbled candy bars over top. Repeat this layer procedure. Chill and store in refrigerator.
Makes a large cake.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix and spread in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Mix 4 ounces shredded American cheese with 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on top of meat.
Bake 10 minutes or more.

title: pineapple-bacon cubes
directions: Cut bacon slices in half and partially cook.
Drain.
Wrap piece of bacon around pineapple chunk; tack with wooden cocktail pick or toothpick.
Broil, turning until bacon is crisp.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a 3 quart pan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat, stirring in the peanut butter until well blended.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream (be sure to only use 1/2).
Pour into pan.
Let cool.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Mix flour, melted margarine and 3/4 cup of the nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream the cheese and sugar together; add 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Layer this on top of cooled crust.
Blend instant pudding and milk thoroughly; let stand until it starts to thicken.
Spread on top of above mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining nuts.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
While it's cooking combine soup, milk, tuna and cheese in a greased casserole dish.
Add cooked pasta and stir until well mixed.
Fold in peas, then top with crushed chips and cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 to 20 minutes until golden brown and bubbly.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, dressing, oil and vanilla at medium speed with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add combination of ingredients alternating with pineapple and banana, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting, if desired.

title: soup beans
directions: Look beans real good to make sure you git* all the rocks and dirt out.
Worsh* 'em* real good over and over (about 3 times) til you know 'em* to be clean.
Put in a big pot.
Cover with water. Add a big hunk of hog meat* and about 2 big spoons of lard.
Cover and cook for about 5 airs* . When the water gits* low, add more til they git* done.
You can tell if'n* they're done when they git* a brown soup on 'em.
That's why they're called "soup beans."
Don't forgit* to add the salt like I did in this recipe.
Put it in at the first.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix; spread bean mix in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with corn or nacho chips.

title: inside out chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, butter, shortening, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in vanilla milk chips and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: meat loaf for the microwave
directions: Combine the following ingredients in a mixing bowl:
ground beef, bread cubes, celery, onion, green pepper, salt, egg and 1/2 cup ketchup.
Mix well and pat evenly into a glass dish.
Brush meat loaf with this mixture:

1/2 cup ketchup, chili powder, brown sugar, lemon juice, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Microwave for 25 to 35 minutes on Medium-high heat or until done. Pour off liquid and let stand covered with foil for 5 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
butter;
add egg yolks and mix well. Mix dry
ingredients.
Add
alternately
with buttermilk; add pineapple, apple butter, jam, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.	Bake at 350° until cake cooks away from sides of pan.
Yield: 4 (8-inch) layers.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Put 1/2 of mixture in casserole dish.
Add layer of Mozzarella; add rest of mixture and top with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk bay clam chowder(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Steam clams in a large covered pot in a small amount of boiling water until they open. Take out the clams as they open and continue to steam the unopened ones a few minutes more.
Discard any clams that do not open.
Shuck clams, then chop and set aside. Reserve 2 cups clam broth from the top of the pan after any sand has settled on the bottom. (Add water, if necessary, to make 2 cups liquid.)

title: dream bars
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Cut butter as for pastry.
Put out on bottom of pan about 10-inches square.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread Part 2 on top.

title: round steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Dredge beef in flour and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown in ovenproof skillet in 2 tablespoons oil.
Remove from pan and make gravy with cornstarch and adjust seasonings.
Add mushrooms with liquid.
Return meat to gravy and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Add water if necessary.

title: pineapple paradise
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions on box.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake according to instructions on box.
Cool cake.

title: milk potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, water, salt, celery and onions.
When tender, add milk, butter or oleo and black pepper.
Bring to simmer. Serve with crackers.

title: apple pizza coffee cake
directions: Into a large bowl combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, 3 tablespoons sugar and salt; mix.
Heat water, milk, oleo and egg; blend into flour.
Knead to soft dough.
Let rise 15 minutes. Shape into ball.
Pat into a 12-inch pizza.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with nuts and raisins.
Cut dough into 10 to 12 pieces. Place over nuts and raisins.
Heat other ingredients in a pan and pour over the frozen dough. Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand for 1 hour outside of the refrigerator in the morning to let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Combine milk and egg whites.
Dip chicken in milk mixture, then cornflakes.
Bake in nonstick pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taffy-nut crunch
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in 3-quart heavy saucepan. Cover and heat to boiling.
Uncover and cook rapidly to 236° on candy thermometer, or soft ball stage.
Stir in nuts slowly, keeping mixture bubbling all the time, then cook rapidly, stirring constantly, to 280° or hard ball stage.
Stir in butter; continue cooking to 300°, or hard crack.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla; sprinkle soda over top quickly, then stir vigorously about 15 seconds, or until mixture is puffy. Pour into buttered jelly-roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Cool completely.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Store in a container with tight fitting lid. Produces approximately 2 1/4 pounds of candy.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked. Add 3 chicken bouillon cubes while boiling. Remove chicken from pan; remove skin, debone and cut into pieces. Save chicken broth. Mix Stove Top stuffing mix packets, butter and 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth (add water if not enough). Break French bread into bite size pieces and mix with Stove Top stuffing mixture. Place stuffing mixture in a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spoon chicken pieces over stuffing. Mix soup with milk. Pour over chicken and stuffing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Stir once halfway through.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This is a good way to use up those broken potato chips.
Sometimes I put 3 or 4 bananas in it, too.

title: chocolate butterscotch scotcheroos
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil
over	medium heat.
Remove from heat;
stir in peanut butter and
then
cereal.	Press
in 13 x 9-inch buttered pan. Spread with
frosting
of butterscotch and chocolate morsels. Heat in microwave
about 4 minutes at Power 5.
Spread frosting.
Chill in refrigerator 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt together.
Beat in evaporated milk, Eagle Brand milk, syrup, water, vanilla and egg yolks.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes, or until pies do not shake in the center.

title: elden's crawfish or shrimp etouffee
directions: Chop onion very fine.
In large pot, add 1/4 stick of butter and chopped onion.
Cook on low heat until onion is brown.
Add remaining ingredients, less the seafood.
Cook 1/2 hour on low heat, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.
Add seafood; cook 1/2 hour on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: salsa dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: holly's mexican corn
directions: Drain corn; cream together cream cheese, margarine and chillies.
Stir corn into creamed mixture and heat slowly.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mix cabbage, green onions, noodles to Top Ramen pack and sunflower seeds.
Mix in the dressing (oil, red wine vinegar, seasoning pack to Top Ramen, garlic salt and pepper).
Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: surprise salad
directions: Stir together and add 1 can drained fruit cocktail.
May use lemon jello and drained pineapple or orange jello and mandarin oranges.

title: chicken and sour cream
directions: Boil chicken and cut in small pieces.
Melt oleo and stir in crushed crackers.
Put half of crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken pieces on top of crumbs.
Mix soup, sour cream and broth together.
Pour over chicken.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pita pizzas
directions: Place pita rounds on baking sheet.
Brush on both sides with 2 tablespoons of oil.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake until golden and crisp (10 minutes).
Heat remaining oil in frying pan.
Add peppers and cook until softened.
Add potatoes and rosemary to peppers.
Heat through, stirring well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Divide the mixture among the pita rounds.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil 3 inches from heat until golden, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: potato pizza supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef.
Add all ingredients except sauce and cheese.
Add sauce and bake 45 minutes to 60 minutes in oven.
Add cheese and bake 15 minutes.

title: tropical pound cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Bake
in Bundt pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit; save the juice.
Mix Tang, pudding and fruit juice together.
Pour over sliced fruit and chill.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, blend soup, milk, mustard and pepper until smooth. Stir in macaroni and 1 1/4 cups cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with onions and remaining cheese. Bake 10 more minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, milk, vanilla flavoring and 1/2 of butter in bowl and mix.
Put in greased dish.
Mix brown sugar, coconut, flour, nuts and remaining butter and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chinese-style vegetables
directions: Cut celery and pepper into thin diagonal slices, each measuring about 1 cup.
Chop onion (3/4 cup) and shred cabbage. Heat oil in skillet; stir in vegetables.
Cover and cook over medium heat until tender.
Sprinkle with salt
and pepper.	Makes 4 servings.

title: snowball cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, lemon juice and undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set, about 45 minutes.
Prepare 2 package of Dream Whip.
Fold into mixture.
Break cake into small pieces.
Place pieces of cake and gelatin mixture in alternate layers in a long sheet cake pan.
As you put layers together, take a spoon and press down.
Chill overnight.
Next day, prepare the other package of Dream Whip and spread over cake.
Sprinkle coconut on cake and add cherries, if you so desire.

title: christmas punch
directions: Beat ice cream and pineapple juice.
Add orange sherbet and ginger ale.
Serves 30.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In large mixer bowl, combine sugar and butter. Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until mixture is creamy, 1 to 2 minutes. Add bananas, eggs and vanilla. Continue beating, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes. In medium bowl, stir together flours, baking soda and salt. Add flour mixture to banana mixture; stir just until moistened. Fold in chocolate chips. Spoon into greased muffin pans. Bake for 18 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: thelma's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with onion, pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until thickened.
Pour over 7 ounce package cooked spaghetti.

title: bootleg baked beans
directions: Dice bacon and fry; when half done, add chopped onion.
When onion is lightly browned, pour off most of the grease.
Add beans, brown sugar, vinegar and catsup.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer very low for about 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole #2
directions: Stir flour in creamed corn.
Drain whole kernel corn.
Add to creamed corn mixture.
Add all other ingredients, adding eggs last.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: ever moist meat loaf
directions: Mix well and form into loaf.
Top with your favorite topping. I use either homemade or canned spaghetti sauce, such as Ragu. Makes a soft, moist meat loaf.

title: salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in pan.
Let come to a boil; reduce heat. Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add salt to taste.
Makes 13 pints. This is chunky salsa.

title: muy delicioso salsa
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the above ingredients.
Store in a covered container and refrigerate.
This can be eaten immediately, however, it is best if stored for 3 days (if you can resist the temptation).
Stores for up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: pie crust pastry
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender until the size of small peas.
Sprinkle water 1 tablespoon at a time over part of the mixture.
Gently mix with a fork.
Push to one side of bowl.
Sprinkle next tablespoon of water and repeat until all is moistened.
Gather with fingers and form into a ball (mix will be crumbly).
Let stand several minutes.
Divide dough into 4 balls.
Flatten slightly and roll on lightly floured surface.
Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In 10-inch iron skillet (on top of stove), melt drippings.
Mix rest of ingredients until blended.
Add drippings.
Pour back into skillet.
Bake 25 minutes or until done.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Pour boiling water over green tomatoes; let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Heat together vinegar, salt, sugar, mustard and celery seed and turmeric.
Add tomatoes, onions, peppers and hot pepper; boil 15 minutes.

title: chocolate "philly" fudge
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill; cut into squares.
Garnish with additional nuts.

title: biscuits(white lily plain flour and mayonnaise biscuits)
directions: Before you start, warm oven to 450°.
Roll out and put in oven to bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
If want darker crust, leave in oven a little longer.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallows and salt.
Cook until mallows melt.
Boil on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove and add chocolate and vanilla.
Beat.
Spread on 9-inch square pan. Chill.

title: noma's molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes on top grate in electric oven.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour. Mix butter, cocoa and water in saucepan. Bring to boil. Pour over flour and sugar, then add buttermilk and baking powder (mixed), eggs and vanilla. Mix well and bake in 11 x 16-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: super beef stew
directions: Melt shortening.
Brown beef cubes; add onion soup mix, tomatoes, water and chili powder.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes. Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook, covered, 45 minutes.

title: apple pizza pie
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle water over mixture and shape into ball.
Roll pastry into 15-inch circle on floured surface.
Place on baking sheet and turn up edge.

title: sweet potato cranberry bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, sweet potatoes, oil and vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to sweet potato mixture, stirring only enough to blend. Fold in cranberries.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and green pepper until tender. Add beans, water, chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered for 10 minutes.

title: economical pea soup joke
directions: Simmer to one pint.
If flavor is too strong, remove pea.

title: peanut butter pie(serves 8)
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Reserve 3 tablespoons for topping.
Fill bottom of pie shell with crumbly mixture.
Prepare pudding from package instructions.
Pour pudding on top of crumbly mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until pudding sets.
Top with Cool Whip and remaining crumbly peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute the onions and peppers in vegetable oil.
Set aside. Mix the cheese with the spaghetti while still hot.
Stir until cheese is melted, then add the tomatoes, mushroom soup, mushrooms, chicken and the sauteed mixture.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable fry
directions: Stick all this, except shortening, in a large bowl.
Mix well. Add to the hot shortening or oil.
Cook, uncovered.
Stir where browned as little as possible so vegetables retain their shape. Cook in large skillet 30 minutes.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Blend together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts; mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll again.

title: jamaican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Set aside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up the squash; mix with soup, onion and cheese.
Arrange in a casserole dish.
Top with pats of butter.
Cook about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put cooked and cut up chicken and drained Veg-All in 12 x 9-inch dish.
Bring broth and soup to boil; pour over chicken. Combine pepper, margarine, flour and buttermilk.
Pour over top of chicken and Veg-All mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Delicious.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix, then drizzle melted butter on top.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold, plain or topped with Cool Whip.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt one stick of butter in casserole dish.
In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour batter into casserole dish on top of melted butter.
Do not stir together. Drain about 1/2 of the juice off the peaches.
Pour peaches and remaining juice into the dish.
Once again, do not stir.
Sprinkle peaches with about 1/4 cup sugar.
Put in oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
The dough mixture will rise to the top.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in ice cream maker or use freezer tray method.
For a variation, add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 3 tablespoons Contreau instead of the lemon juice.
Serves 8.

title: peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in square 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake until peaches are tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Make sauce with beef, onions, tomato sauce and water.
In shallow baking dish, arrange three alternate layers of cooked noodles, cottage cheese, sauce and other cheeses.
Sprinkle Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; let stand 15 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients, sprinkle with salt and let stand 2 hours in a colander to drain.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Cook 30-40 minutes over medium heat.

title: carrot and cabbage salad
directions: Toss all together and add Miracle Whip.

title: mexican finger cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in small square casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt the cream cheese and tomato soup together over a low to medium heat.
Remove from heat and cool a little.
Stir in the mayonnaise, mixing until smooth.
Melt the gelatine in a small amount of water, then add to the cream cheese mixture.
Stir in the celery, green onions and shrimp, mixing until well blended. Pour into mold.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: strawberry yogurt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cake pans.
Beat cake mix, water, oil, eggs and one container of yogurt in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into cake pans and bake about 35 minutes or until top springs back.
Cool completely.
Add together Cool Whip and one container of strawberry yogurt.
Spread over the cooled cake and garnish with strawberries. Refrigerate.

title: pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot shortening.
Drain off drippings.
Pour around pork chops a mixture of chicken soup, pet milk, and water.
Add onion.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Keep gravy stirred well.

title: "tex-mex" kasha
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion, celery, pepper and garlic.
Saute until onion is soft.
Stir in oregano, cumin and chili powder along with kasha and tomatoes.
Season to taste with pepper.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer about 20 minutes until liquid has been absorbed and kasha is cooked.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let cheese melt about 1 minute.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato soup, water and spices and simmer while you cook the noodles.
(Stir occasionally.)
Drain noodles.
Spray Pam (or grease) a square baking dish and layer meat, cheese, noodles and cheese until meat is gone.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven until cheese bubbles.

title: apple cake with hot caramel sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop pecans finely.
Peel, core and chop apples to equal 2 1/2 cups.
Chop the size of thumbnail.
Set aside.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and sausage in a skillet; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until rice is absorbed.
Add water, if necessary.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan. In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour 1/2 of batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes.
If desired, dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken pecan spectacular
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for about 1 hour.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Slice carrots; salt and cook until tender.
Drain. Toss carrots; slice separated onions and bell pepper together. Combine all other ingredients and pour over carrots mixture. Chill.

title: red raspberry ring salad
directions: Drain raspberries, reserve syrup.
Dissolve jello in water. Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Stir in lemonade concentrate and reserved syrup.
Chill until partially set, then add raspberries and pecans.
Put in mold and chill until set.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except grated cheeses.
Spread into a shallow baking dish. Cover mixture first with a layer of Jack cheese and then a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Mix the rest of ingredients until creamy.
Add nuts, if desired.
Serve with apples, nuts, bananas, pears or any of your favorite fruits.
Warm slightly in microwave before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts in slow cooker overnight on low.
Use a food processor to chop chicken, almonds and celery.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Use salt, white pepper and mayonnaise to your liking.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight. Just before eating, add shoestring potatoes, any amount you want.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and eggs, then add sugar.
Mix dry ingredients. Blend in cream and then add flour and the rest of the ingredients. Before adding nuts, dredge them in 1/4 cup flour.
Dough will be very stiff.
Refrigerate overnight for easier handling when rolling into balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
This makes a big batch; may want to halve recipe.

title: vegetable stick
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together mayonnaise, cream cheese and Hidden Valley.
Spread on crust and top with broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, onion and cooked crisp bacon (chopped fine).
Top with grated cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all together in pan. Top with 1 layer of pepperoni, then top with cheese.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, pepper and peas into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix Miracle Whip and sugar; spread over lettuce mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and top with bacon.
Better if set overnight.

title: custard
directions: Mix and add slowly 2 cups scalded milk and vanilla to the eggs, sugar and salt.
Pour into a buttered baking dish; set in a pan of warm water.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: white bean chili
directions: Saute onion in oil; stir in chilies, garlic, oregano, cumin and chili powder. Saute for another 5 minutes. Add the white beans, broth, tomatoes, cilantro and lime juice. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and add chicken. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Note:
I usually make a double batch, using 3/4 cup shortening and 3/4 cup margarine.
This makes them crack better.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix baking soda with berries.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake in two cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Then add Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips and spread over top. Refrigerate only until topping is set or leave out overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, sour milk and dissolved baking soda.
Add flour, nuts and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in greased loaf pan.

title: wedding punch
directions: In a 5-quart punch bowl, pour in juice.
Then add lemon juice. In another container mix jello, sugar and hot water.
Stir until all ingredients are dissolved.
Add cold water.
Add this mixture to punch bowl.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Sherbet can also be added if desired.
Different color jello makes different color punch:
cherry for red, lemon for yellow, orange for peach and lime for green.
Yields 25 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; add onion and celery.
Cook until tender (not brown); add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Serve over toasted buns.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish. Mix sugar, flour and milk and pour over margarine. Pour peaches in center and bake in preheated oven at 370° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, chopped onion, dried beef and Worcestershire sauce; mix thoroughly.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap and chill for approximately 2 hours before serving.
(Can be frozen.)
Serve with crackers or vegetables. Serves approximately 15.
Great for parties!

title: zucchini casserole gourmet
directions: Saute zucchini and eggplant in oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain.
Stir in next 8 ingredients and heat thoroughly. Turn into greased baking dish and top with tomato sauce and cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 1 big or 2 small casserole dishes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.
Cover dish with foil while baking and remove to brown lightly.
Can be mixed and placed in refrigerator overnight or frozen and baked later.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Blend soup, milk and chicken.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: jelly roll
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line bottom with wax paper.
Grease paper.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Beat eggs in medium size bowl with electric mixer at high speed until thick and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly, until mixture is very thick.
(This will take 5 to 7 minutes.)
Stir in water and vanilla.
Fold in flour mixture. Spread batter evenly into pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto a large damp towel.
Roll towel and cake together and leave 3 minutes.
Unroll, remove towel and spread filling in center of cake.
Roll and dust with powdered sugar.

title: dark sweet fruitcake
directions: Grease and flour sides and bottom of 12 cup Bundt pan or 10-inch angel food pan.
In a large bowl, combine eggs and water. Add remaining ingredients by hand, stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes, remove from pan, cool completely.

title: hearty egg scramble
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter until crisp-tender.
Add potatoes and ham.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Melt butter; add cocoa and Cola. Heat to boiling point; cool slightly.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture; stir until blended.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy cheese puffs
directions: Cream butter.
Add cheese, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add pepper and form into a ball.
Chill for 2 hours.
Shape into small 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove carefully.
Store in airtight container. Yields 40.

title: apples squares
directions: Mix
first
11	ingredients
together.	Mix applesauce, oil, eggs
and
milk; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Mix dry mixture
with applesauce mixture and mix well.
Spray 14 x 10 x 1-inch
sheet
with Pam and line with wax paper;
pour in batter.

title: fried corn
directions: Husk and silk corn; cut from cob.
Heat bacon fat until sizzling.
Add corn, salt, pepper and enough water to cover corn. Cook 20 minutes covered.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Place cherries and pineapple in cake pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix (dry) over cherries and pineapple.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Cook in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade(yields 8 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate meat overnight.
Remove from marinade and grill or broil.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar to desired consistency.
For eight people.
Yields one 9-inch cake.

title: apple pie delight
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a mixing bowl, combine Equal, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry mixture to apples and toss. Fill pastry-lined pie plate with apple mixture; dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust.
Seal, flute edges and cut slits on the top crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Add sugar to melted butter; mix well.
Add egg and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and salt that have been sifted together. Add sesame seed.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Drop by 1/4 teaspoon onto foil.
Space about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Watch closely.
Remove from foil when slightly cooled.
Use foil only once.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together sugars and syrups in saucepan.
Bring to boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Add flavoring and cereal.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper; cool.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and cook until tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain and cool.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Brown ground sirloin; if using

a different cut of meat, be sure to drain off excess fat. Add in the can of diced tomatoes and the taco seasoning mix. Stir and heat. In a casserole dish, first layer the refried beans. Next, spoon the meat mixture over the beans. Smooth the sour cream over the meat mixture. Sprinkle the Cheddar cheese over the sour cream. Garnish the dip with the diced tomatoes, black olives, jalapeno slices and scallions. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.
(Or cook other ingredients before adding to macaroni and cheese.)

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then add nuts, partially thawed relish and water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
While the bread is still warm, pour about 1/8 cup orange juice over it.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: In skillet saute onions in butter until soft, not brown.
Add ground meat.
Cook, breaking meat up, while cooking.
In a 2-quart buttered casserole dish, layer the carrots, half of the cabbage and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add meat mixture; press down slightly.
Add remaining cabbage.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Combine first 8 ingredients in medium bowl and season with salt and pepper.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon crab mixture into each mushroom.
Place in prepared baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over. Bake until mushrooms are tender and cheese melts, about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: beef and vegetables
directions: Cut fat from meat and slice into 1/4-inch slices as for stir-fry.
Stir or fry meat until brown in large pan.
Add vegetables and 1 quart of water.
Simmer until tender.

title: nothing to snicker at snickers pie
directions: Butter an 8-inch pie plate.
In a medium bowl combine the graham cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir in the butter until well combined.
Press the crumb mixture into the bottom and sides of the pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until set.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Cut 4 of the Snickers bars in half lengthwise and then into 1/4 inch pieces crosswise. Sprinkle the pieces in the bottom of the pie crust.
Prepare the pudding mix according to the package directions for pie filling. Spoon the filling over the Snickers pieces in the pie shell.
Cover the surface of the pie with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: fried perch
directions: Season fish with garlic salt and onion powder.
Mix egg, milk and Tabasco.
Stir in flour, salt and mustard and beat until smooth.
Coat fish in batter and fry in hot oil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Mix until sugar dissolves (don't heat).
Place approximately 2-quarts sliced pickling cucumbers in a large jar.
Cover with sugar mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will be ready to eat in two days.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook granulated sugar and milk slowly for 10 minutes or until it forms a soft ball.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy and pour in pan to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set aside 3 slices ham.
Finely chop remaining ham and combine with remaining ingredients and shape into ball.
Cover ball with 3 leftover slices of ham.

title: white cloud punch
directions: Mix fluids and then put in sherbet and ice cream last.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan.
Sprinkle crushed vanilla wafers over margarine.
Next, sprinkle coconut, then chocolate chips, then sprinkle butterscotch chips, then sprinkle chopped pecans. Pour sweetened condensed milk over other ingredients.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Heat to dissolve on top of stove.
After mixture heats, add sausages and cook for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and sugar. Cut in shortening. In a bowl, beat together the egg and milk. Pour into dry ingredients. Stir well with a fork. Spread into an 8-inch greased pan. Add topping.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add the vinegar, oil, vanilla and cold water; stir.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix flour, oats, sugar, lemon peel and soda.
Reserve one cup of mixture for topping.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
Place in ungreased pan in oven preheated to 350°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and carefully spread sauce on baked crust.
Stir nuts into reserved oat-flour mix and pat lightly into sauce.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes more, until top is golden.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 24.
Freezes well.

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat together milk, Crisco and sugar.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Use self-rising flour to make biscuit-like dough.
Let rise to double and roll out.
Dip in oil and put in pan to rise again to double and bake.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Mix well in center. Pour pumpkin mixture in, and stir just until dry mixture is moistened. Stir in cranberries. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit 'n buttermilk shakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender, whirl for 20 to 30 seconds.
Pour in chilled glasses.

title: caramel cups
directions: Mix by hand or pastry cutter.
Make balls and press into tassie pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: In a double boiler melt chocolate chips with corn syrup and water.
Remove from water; add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Drop on a foil covered cookie sheet.
Decorate with cinnamon candies.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach, and remove any dark leaves or large bitter ones. Add onion, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon olive oil; toss lightly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove from bones.
Reserve 2 to 3 cups of broth.
Cook spaghetti in remaining broth until done or tender.
Melt 1/4 stick of butter in heavy skillet and cook onion, pepper and celery.
Add chicken and cream of chicken soup.
Add drained spaghetti and broth.
Cook for about 20 minutes or until it thickens.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and egg yolks.
Beat in flour and milk alternately.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and bake.

title: broccoli pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, parsley, basil and garlic;
mix well. Add
cheese, broccoli and noodles; mix lightly.
Chill. Arrange tomatoes on platter; top with salad.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
In a 2-cup measure, put 1 cup cold water, then 1 cup mayonnaise and vanilla. Add this to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of pan.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, milk, vanilla and salt.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Makes enough icing for two 8-inch or 9-inch layers.

title: peanut cream dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until thoroughly blended. Serve over finely shredded cabbage.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries. Add chopped cherries and pecans to pineapple.
Heat juice to boiling.
Add Jell-O and cheese to hot juice.
Beat with electric mixer. Add solid ingredients.
Pour in Coke and stir lightly.
Pour mixture into large container and refrigerate until congealed.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, oleo and milk to a rolling boil in heavy saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to keep from sticking.
Add peanut butter and stir until well blended.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Stir until well blended and creamy.
Spread into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook meat until it is tender enough to shred.
In another pan, cook green pepper and onions in oil.
Stir in chili powder and cook 1 minute.
Add meat and remaining ingredients plus 1 cup of water and 1 cup ketchup.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Shred meat with 2 forks.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fudge ribbon surprise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate in 2/3 cup water; stir.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; cook and stir until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Cool.
In small bowl, beat cheese and 2 tablespoons shortening until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in 1 egg, 2 tablespoons water and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
In large bowl, beat remaining 1 1/4 cups sugar and 1/2 cup shortening until fluffy. Add remaining 3 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: sweet and sour sausages
directions: Combine jelly, barbecue sauce and meat in a crock-pot or slow cooker on low heat for 4 to 6 hours.
This makes a wonderful appetizer for large get togethers.
Leftover sauce may be frozen for future use.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion 30 to 40 minutes in water.
Drain.
Add butter; mash.
Beat egg, add to squash mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Butter casserole dish; layer squash, cheese, squash and cheese.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk, stirring constantly. Set aside.

title: "rocks"(christmas cookies)
directions: Cream
the
butter
and
sugar.
Add
the
eggs.
Sift together the flour,
cinnamon,
cloves and salt and add to the butter-sugar-egg mixture.
Dissolve the baking soda in the hot water and add
to
the mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients. Foil line and grease a cookie sheet.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls. Bake at
for
12 minutes or until nicely browned. Makes a gross (144 cookies).

title: sour cream cake
directions: Filling:
Cream the margarine and sugar together. Add one egg at a time and beat well.
Add flour and sour cream alternately. Beat egg whites stiff and add last. Bake cake at 350° or until done (about 1 hour).

title: nacho dip(microwave)
directions: Cube the cheese and mix in with the chili.
Put in a microwave container and microwave on High for about 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir and microwave more if needed, until cheese is melted.
Put on nacho chips.
Can also be placed in a small crock-pot and melted down this way.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and bananas.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) for 1 hour.
(Watch baking time, it will depend on your oven.)
Good with cream cheese for tea sandwiches.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a heavy pan.
Bring to full rolling boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate bits until melted.
Add Marshmallow Fluff, vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature before cutting.

title: pumpkin-pine nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In a medium size bowl, mix eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well, then add pumpkin.
Mix well and fold into dry ingredients.
Add pine nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans and bake for 45 minutes.

title: cajun seasoning mix
directions: Put all ingredients into processor.
Process at grind until blended.
This combination of spices will give any recipe that spice New Orleans flavor.

title: strawberry glaze cheesecake
directions: Combine and press firmly into bottom of buttered spring-form pan.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo.
Boil over med heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Beat egg whites 2 minutes. Pour in half of syrup and mix well.
Boil rest of syrup until mixture reaches hard ball stage.
Pour over egg whites and beat. Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture looses it gloss.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool completely and cut into 1 inch squares.

title: oriental salad
directions: Finely shred each 1/2 cabbage.
Thaw and add peas.
Drain and chop chestnuts and add; add cashews.
Toss lightly.
Stir soy sauce into the mayonnaise.
Dress salad if serving immediately, otherwise hold the dressing until just before serving because the soy sauce will cause wilting.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix as in any pudding.

title: potato-vegetable saute
directions: In an 8 or 9-inch skillet, heat oil; add onion and garlic and saute until onion is soft.
Add potatoes and bell peppers; saute, stirring until potatoes are lightly browned and peppers are tender-crisp.
Stir in salt and pepper and saute for 2 minutes longer.
Makes 2 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat the broth, salt and garlic in a heavy saucepan to boiling.
Stir in the rice.
Cover and simmer until the liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the lemon zest and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Remove the garlic. Gently stir in the dill and butter.
Season to taste with pepper. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 portions.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Mix oil and dressing. Toss with pretzels. Toss every 15 minutes until liquid is gone.

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture in a lightly oiled 10 x 15 x 1 1/2-inch pan and bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and while hot spoon mixture into powdered sugar.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts and put on waxed paper to cool.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: taco nacho
directions: Season ground beef with salt, chili powder, garlic powder, cumin and black pepper.
On cookie sheet, place a single layer of chips.
Top each with a slice of cheese.
Add one tablespoon of ground beef and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes or until topping is hot and cheese is bubbling.
Remove and top each snack with a tablespoon of cold guacamole.
Serve immediately.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: west virginia black walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand until syrupy.
Beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg. Stir in alternately with apples and sugar mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare pudding and Dream Whip as directed on packages.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Peel and cut up apples, oranges and bananas.
Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill. Recipe can be halved.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in hot fat until golden.
Add meat and seasonings. Brown.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes.
Add milk, egg and seasoning.
Spoon mounds of potatoes over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon about 2-inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Keep hot.
Meanwhile, melt butter, stir in flour and seasonings.
(Do not brown.) Stir in milk.
Cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until it melts.
Pour cheese sauce over macaroni and stir to coat. Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: health salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in 1 cup boiling water.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in cabbage, carrots, celery and salad dressing. Chill.
Serves 8.

title: spicy sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix together sugar, flour, spices and salt in a large bowl. Stir in eggs. Add sweet potatoes and milk and beat until smooth. Pour into pastry shell. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center removes clean. If crust browns too quickly, cover with foil strips. Serves 8.

title: pheasant stir-fry
directions: Cut the pheasant breasts into bite size pieces.
Stir-fry the pheasant in a very hot wok with 1 tablespoon oil, stirring until the meat is cooked (5 to 7 minutes).
Add water and bouillon. Stir in cornstarch.
Keep stirring and cook until thickened.
Put into another container and set aside.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Shred dried beef.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
I use a hand mixer.
Put in bowl and serve with crackers.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, peppers, onions, and thawed peas. You may add egg slices and chopped ham layered if desired. Seal vegetables with a mixture of mayonnaise and sugar. Top this with a layer of cheddar cheese and a layer of bacon crumbled.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cut carrots into bite-size chunks.
Cook crisp, not too soft; drain.
Slice onion and green pepper into rings.
Add these to carrots.
Mix in pan remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil 1 minute; pour over vegetables.
Let set overnight.

title: tortilla bites
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and chopped green chilies.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up.
Slice into 4 to 5 sections.
Serve hot or cold with picante sauce.

title: five spice roast chicken
directions: In a 2 to 3-cup pan, combine oil and 5-spice.
Cook over medium heat; stir until hot.
Add soy sauce, sugar, sherry and garlic.
Place chicken, breast side up, on roasting rack in shallow baking pan.
Rub generously with 5-spice mixture.
Place remaining mixture inside cavity of chicken.
Roast at 375° until thigh bone is no longer pink (approximately 1 3/4 hours).
Drain juices from chicken and place on serving platter.
Scrape baking pan; stir with drained juice and heat.
Stir in green onions and pour over each serving.
Serves 6.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Set aside cornmeal for topping.
Combine 2 cups flour with rest of dry ingredients.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with cornmeal. Cover; let rise at least 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove loaf immediately.
Good toasted.

title: mounds cake and frosting
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add cocoa, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: those potatoes
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix together 1/4 cup butter, soup, cheese, sour cream, salt and onion and pour over potatoes. Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chickens and roast until done.
Grind chickens and lean meat.
Grind onions and potatoes.
Set meat aside.
Combine onions, potatoes, beans and tomatoes.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add kernel corn, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, lemon juice and pepper.
Cook and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cream-style corn and meat.
Simmer for at least 1 hour, stirring regularly.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese.
Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
When ready to serve, stir in 1 large bottle Catalina dressing and 1 medium bag Fritos corn chips.
May also add hamburger meat to mixture.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: This is the old-fashioned way!
If it is too sweet, use less sugar.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Peel apples and chop chunky.
Mix other ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples until coated.
Pour into pie crust.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Cut carrots in strips; peel and quarter potatoes.
Combine all ingredients (do not brown meat).
Put into a 3-quart casserole. Bake, covered in 325° oven for 3 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: honey grilled chicken(low-fat)
directions: Cut peppers into 2-inch pieces.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a large, heavy-duty plastic bag; add chicken and peppers.
Seal bag and shake bag until chicken and peppers are well coated.
Marinate in refrigerator 3 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Remove chicken and peppers from marinade.
Place marinade in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray.
Place rack on grill over medium coals, (300° to 350°).
Place chicken on rack. Grill, covered, 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until chicken is done, basting frequently with marinade during the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Transfer chicken to a serving platter; keep warm.

title: swiss chicken(light and real easy)
directions: *Can use two slices of low-fat toast, ground up in a food processor.

title: cabbage rolls ala fingers
directions: Mix well in a large bowl raw ground chuck, rice, onion, salt, pepper, celery, green pepper and garlic with a little tomato juice to moisten.

Remove core from cabbage, then place cabbage in boiling water to wilt leaves so that they can be easily rolled. Place about 1/2 cup meat mixture into cabbage leaf and roll. Fasten with toothpick if necessary.
Alternate layers of sauerkraut and rolls in large kettle.
Pour can of tomatoes over top and with spoon, let tomatoes seep through layers.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 2 1/2 hours.
Add tomato juice if rolls become dry.

title: citrus spinach salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill thoroughly.
Combine spinach, orange sections and onion rings in a salad bowl.
Drizzle dressing over spinach mixture.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle with pine nuts before serving.

title: chicken divine
directions: Layer thawed broccoli and chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice together. Spread over broccoli and chicken layers.
Add cheese and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: bobbi's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add cream of chicken soup and Kraft hot cheese, mixing together over low heat until well blended. Add cooked rice and cooked broccoli and mix well in large bowl.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Bias slice carrots 1/2-inch thick.
Cook and drain.
Combine all ingredients; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots and serve.

title: dad's cookies(makes 8 dozen cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
If you chill dough first, it will not spread as much.

title: strawberries bonaparte
directions: Thaw pastry sheet at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Unfold pastry on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 3 strips along fold marks.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden.
Remove from baking sheet and cool on wire rack.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk. Mix thoroughly. Shape into balls. Melt shortening in large skillet; brown and cook meatballs. Remove meatballs; place in crock-pot or casserole. Mix cornstarch and brown sugar. Stir in reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth. Pour into skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir for 1 minute. Add pineapple and green peppers. Pour over meatballs and cook on low in crock-pot or 30 minutes in 300° oven. Serve over cooked rice.

title: noodle clusters
directions: Melt the chocolate chips in a microwave safe bowl. Once melted, stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by cluster shapes on wax paper. Chill until set.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar in bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in flat pan.
Mix onion soup mix and sour cream.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Spoon mushroom soup over this.
Top with mushrooms and juice.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Uncover and sprinkle almonds on top.
Continue baking, uncovered for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: two tomato pasta salad
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water for 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Cook pasta; drain.
Heat olive oil in a skillet; saute garlic well.
Toss in green onion and broccoli and saute for a couple of minutes more.
Blend vinegar with the herbs, pepper and hot sauce.
Gently toss with the broccoli mixture and pasta.
Add tomatoes and cheese.
Add salt.
Remember the Parmesan is salty tasting.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix buttermilk, mayonnaise, salt, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, garlic, pepper and Tabasco.
Mix until smooth.
Toss with macaroni, carrots, parsley, green onion, dill weed, cucumber and radishes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Put these ingredients in prepared 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Add to chicken and put in casserole dish.
Put cheese and bread crumbs on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add evaporated milk, butter and vanilla. Boil in double boiler until thick.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread vanilla wafers over bottom of pan.
Slice bananas over wafers. When pudding has thickened and cooled, pour over wafers and bananas and refrigerate.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cornstarch, salt and water in a large bowl and mix well.
Dip the beef steaks into the batter and fry in 2-inches of oil until nicely browned.
Remove to a platter and keep warm.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt butter; add onion and cook on low heat until onion is transparent.
This may also be microwaved.
Take off heat.
Add beef consomme, water and mushrooms.
Stir.
Add rice.
Mix well. Pour into casserole and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be reheated.

title: george sr.'s smoky barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to the point of boiling for 1 minute.
Lower the flame quickly and simmer half an hour to an hour or until onions are done.

title: lime mist salad
directions: Heat applesauce and dissolve gelatin in it.
Add 7-Up; stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Combine marshmallows, cheese and cream.
Chill overnight.
The next day, beat marshmallow mixture until thick.
Spread over salad.
Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed clam dip
directions: Put stuffing mix in bowl; add clam liquid (gradually).
Let stand until liquid is absorbed.
Add parsley, lemon juice, Worcestershire and seasonings.
Melt margarine in small pan; add chopped celery and onions and saute until soft.
Add this mixture to stuffing mix and lastly the clams.
Mix well.
Put in casserole; top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in moderate oven until hot.

title: quick and easy bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of an 8 x 10-inch glass Pyrex.
Spread vegetarian chili over cream cheese.
Spread cheese over chili.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time and beat well after
each.
Add
vanilla.
Add
corn syrup and mix just long enough
to mix.
Stir in pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes until set (center will not jiggle). This pie is not real sweet.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add tomato soup, garlic salt, onion salt, oregano and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Butter
a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread noodles over the bottom. Pour
meat sauce
over
the noodles and sprinkle the shredded cheeses
over the top.
Cover with foil and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Melt in heavy pot 1 1/2 tablespoons butter and 1 1/2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Add and simmer chopped onions and paprika.
Simmer until shiny and red.
Add salt and chicken stock. When broth comes to a boil, add chicken.
Simmer covered until tender, about 1 hour.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: escalloped cabbage with cheese sauce
directions: Cook until tender; drain and put in a baking dish.

title: scallops in herb-butter sauce
directions: In 8-inch square dish, combine butter, basil, rosemary and salt.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until butter is melted. Stir in scallops and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spoon butter mixture over scallops.
Cover completely with plastic wrap.
Cook at Medium for 7 to 8 minutes.
Scallops should be tender.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and margarine in a mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until just combined.
Drop 2 tablespoons of cookie dough per cookie onto lightly buttered cookie sheets.
Space cookies 2 inches apart and flatten slightly.
Bake 20 minutes or until cookies appear dry but are soft to the touch.
Cool 3 minutes before transferring to a rack.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place oven on 400° and bake for 30 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch or two 8 x 8-inch pans.

title: crab meat mousse
directions: Heat soup in saucepan. Dissolve gelatin in water. Stir all ingredients into soup. Pour into mold sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Refrigerate until set. Garnish with paprika and sprigs of parsley.

title: tofu chocolate pudding
directions: Blend in food processor or blender until smooth and creamy. Pour into individual serving dishes or baked pie shell.
Chill until firm and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender and slice.
Boil broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
For sauce combine chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Lay broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay chicken over broccoli.
Spread sauce over chicken. Place shredded cheese over sauce.
Top with toasted bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ham delight
directions: Mix all (except rolls) together.
Remove rolls from tin trays and using a sharp knife, split rolls in half.
Spread ham mixture between the rolls and place back in pans.
Cover with tin foil, warm on 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (don't overheat).
Let cool before cutting rolls apart.

title: tarragon chicken salad(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Arrange the chicken breasts in a single layer in a large baking pan and spread the Creme Fraiche or cream evenly over them.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from the oven and allow to cool in the cream.
Shred the meat into bite-size pieces and transfer to a bowl.
Discard the cream. Whisk the sour cream and mayonnaise together in a small bowl and pour over the chicken.
Add the celery, walnuts, tarragon and salt and pepper and toss well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Correct the seasoning before serving.

title: charles' banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas and wafers.
Make 3 layers of wafers and bananas in casserole dish.
Pour pudding mixture over them.
Beat 2 egg whites until peaks form.
Beat in 3 tablespoons sugar and beat.
Spread over pudding.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: easy cheese danish
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 glass pan with butter flavored cooking spray. Roll out 1 can of crescent rolls in the bottom of the pan.
Soften cream cheese in microwave for 45 seconds.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk with mixer until smooth.
Spread mixture onto crescent rolls.
Top with second can of crescent rolls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool for 5 minutes and serve warm.

title: festive pork roast
directions: Cut a slit lengthwise through center of pork, not all the way through.
Lay flat.
Rub with garlic, salt and pepper to taste; sprinkle with raisins.
Close roast and tie with string.
Place rosemary on top.
Wrap roast with heavy duty foil.
Poke several small holes through foil into pork on all sides.
Place in roasting pan.
Roast in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: beef steak
directions: Marinate steaks in lemon juice, soy sauce and pepper. Pan fry in 2 tablespoons oil. When cooked, remove from pan onto a serving dish. Add 2 teaspoons oil to pan and fry onions until tender. Pile on top of steaks.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients, then add the nuts, dates, coconut and well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Spread the mixture about 1/2 inch thick in a buttered pan.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes. Remove pan from oven.
Cut cake into strips while still warm and roll pieces in granulated sugar; or roll into balls, then into sugar.
This makes 4 dozen or more.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form a crust in a 10-inch pie plate.
Add ground beef to spaghetti sauce and heat.
Spread cottage or Ricotta cheese over spaghetti.
Cover with beef sauce mix.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: granola - traditional
directions: This is base.
Everything else is optional and can be added in any combination:
coconut, nuts, sunflower seeds and flavorings (orange oil and vanilla).
Mix with enough water to easily mix. Spread on large cookie sheet or jelly-roll pans.
Bake slowly in 325° oven, stirring frequently to evenly bake until light brown. Remove from oven; cool and add any combination of:
dried frut, chopped dates, apricots, raisins, chocolate or carob chips.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Put salad mix in bowl, then add eggs, onions and peas. Combine mayonnaise and sugar; spread over top, sealing edges. Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss just before serving.

title: tampa bay shrimp(microwave)
directions: Cut pepper into 1-inch strips.
Chop onion. Coat the bottom of a microwave-safe dish with the oil.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cover.
Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: scott's cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese at room temperature.
While preparing other ingredients, drain pineapple but not moistless.
Mix everything together.
Roll ball in nuts.
Refrigerate.
Add 1 cup pecans, if desired, and mix into ball.

title: broiled catfish fillets
directions: Season the fillets with salt and pepper to taste.
Put oleo in shallow baking dish in hot (400° to 500°) oven until the oleo is browned.
This gives a distinctive flavor.
Place fillets upside down in sizzling hot oleo and return to oven for 7 to 10 minutes. Turn with spatula and baste.
Sprinkle each piece with lemon juice, wine, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Return to oven until done (approximately 5 minutes).
Run under broiler quickly.
Baste fish with sauce and serve in sauce.
Garnish with fresh dill.
Serves 4.

title: wassail
directions: Heat apple juice and one cinnamon stick to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer for 5 minutes, covered.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cinnamon sticks; simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve warm using remaining cinnamon sticks as individual stirrers.

title: beets(over 50 years old)
directions: Cook and stir the first 4 ingredients in the top of a double boiler.
When clear, add the beets and place the pan, covered, over hot water for 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, heat the beets again and add the butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tipsy orange and ginger sweet
directions: *We would call these either ginger biscuits or ginger nuts in England.

title: miniature meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into small balls (about the size of a marble).
Broil until brown; turn once.
Drain.

title: good luck best pie crust
directions: With a fork, mix together first 4 ingredients. In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures.
Stir with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into ball with hands. Chill at least 15 minutes. Roll into desired shape or it can be frozen for later use.
Makes two 9-inch double crusts or three 8-inch shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cocoon cookies
directions: Shape batter into a cocoon shape.
While warm, roll in 10x sugar.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes on bottom rack, then 15 minutes on middle rack.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Mix French dressing, onion soup mix and marmalade together. Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in oven about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove foil about the last 20 minutes of cooking time.
Serve with rice.

title: crab dip elegante
directions: Melt cream cheese over low heat, stirring constantly.
Blend in mayonnaise, garlic, onion, mustard, sugar and salt.
Stir in crab and wine; heat through.
Makes about 2 cups.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together, refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chocolate milk
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add a little hot water to make a paste.
Add the rest of water.
Boil one minute and cool.
Serve with milk (add 2 tablespoons of mixture to 8 ounce glass of cold milk, or hot milk).

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Cook onion in butter about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally until tender. Stir in rice.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in broth and salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring once or twice; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 16 minutes (do not lift cover and stir); remove from heat.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add 1 small can creamed corn.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use a greased iron skillet to bake in (8 to 9-inch pan).

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples and place in a glass baking dish.
Pour water (or juice) over apples.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and cinnamon well.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Pour on top of apples evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yummy!

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs and butter.
Pour 1/2 of crumbs into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip Cool Whip and cream cheese with sugar.
Put 1/2 of this on top of buttered crumbs.
Pour pie filling over this.
Add other half of Cool Whip and cream cheese. Top with remaining crumbs.
Cool until ready to serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Coat 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Place croutons in dish and coat with margarine.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the croutons.
Mix milk, eggs and mustard and pour over cheese and crouton mixture.
Sprinkle bacon crumbs evenly over dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Allow to stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: blender fudge pie
directions: In container of electric blender, combine eggs, sugar, milk, margarine, cocoa and vanilla.
Whir
on high speed for 2 minutes. Divide between the two pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center of pie is "shaky."
Cool to room temperature.
Yields 2 pies.

title: minestrone main dish soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown bacon, onion, celery, garlic and basil until tender.
Stir in soups, water, salt, tomatoes and pasta.
Bring to boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and zucchini.
Cook 10 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 cups.

title: oven-fried fish (diabetic)
directions: Combine corn flakes, celery salt, onion powder, paprika, and pepper.
Dip fish in milk; roll in corn flake mixture.
Place fish in nonstick baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes until brown.
Yield
6 - 2 oz. servings.
Each serving may be exchanged for 1/2 bread - 2 low-fat meat.

title: cold lemon souffle
directions: Stir gelatin into warmed milk until dissolved.
Combine egg yolks, lemon juice, lemon rind, sugar and gelatin mixture in the top of a double boiler.
Heat, stirring until thickened.
Cool pan in a bowl of ice, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Whip cream.
Fold egg whites and whipped cream into the thickened lemon mixture.
Spoon into a souffle dish and chill until set.
Serve cold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh neckbones and spaghetti
directions: Place neckbones in pot; cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Cook over low flame, simmering until neckbones are done, then add spaghetti and cook until tender.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion soup over rice.
Place pieces of chicken, skin side up, over rice.
Mix soups with water, mix well and pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 2 hours, or until rice is tender.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda, and salt.
Cream together shortening and peanut butter, gradually add the two sugars. Creaming well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend the dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.

Bake at 375° for 8 minutes, then remove from oven and place a solid milk chocolate candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so cookie cracks around the edge. Return to oven and bake 2 - 5 minutes longer.

title: apricot nectar delight jell-o salad
directions: Add ingredients and put in refrigerator to set.

title: split pea soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding, then add pineapple and the juice, then the marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt stick of margarine and combine with mushroom soup and sour cream.
Add squash and rest of ingredients.
Bake in a large, flat dish or 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli and cauliflower supreme
directions: Steam broccoli and cauliflower 4 minutes and drain. Place in a shallow, greased 2 qt. dish. Sprinkle sharp cheese over veggies. Pour mixture of milk and soup over this layer. Place Velveeta cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with onion rings. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: summer champagne
directions: Mix sugar and water in saucepan; bring to boil.
Cook for 5 minutes; cool.
Add fruit juices to syrup; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour into 6 (10 ounce) glasses.
Garnish with cherries, strawberries or pineapple chunks.

title: margarita pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine condensed milk, lime juice, tequila, food coloring and Triple Sec.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crumb crust.
Freeze 4 hours. Whip 1 cup whipping cream for topping and add just before serving.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, onion, 2 tablespoons margarine, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Combine other crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: matt's breakfast delight
directions: First, get a bowl.
Pour in some corn flakes.
Add some sugar and milk.
Stir 3 times and eat.

title: brandy slush
