directions: Heat on medium.
Put frozen orange juice and lemonade.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups of brandy.
Freeze 24 hours.
Dip into glass.
Pour 7-Up over.
Very good summer slush.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients with spaghetti.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt esther's fruit salad with frosting
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add juice of lemon and cold water.
When partially thickened, add well drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into ovenproof glass dish.
Chill. When firm, top with frosting.

title: cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until syrupy.
Mix cranberries until soft and add to Jell-O.
Add pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: english style mint sauce
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt in a small saucepan.
Bring to boil; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in mint and vinegar.
Set sauce aside to cool to room temperature before serving.
Flavor will increase with standing.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: pork or beef roast and gravy
directions: Salt roast on both sides.
Put in roaster and cover with both cans of soup and Coke.
Bake at 400° until tender.
Gravy is made while roast bakes.

title: cereal cookies
directions: To make these cookies you will need 2 mixing bowls.
Mix honey and peanut butter together in one of the mixing bowls. Add 1 cup of cereal.

Stir into the honey and peanut butter mixture. Put 2 cups of cereal into the second mixing bowl. With your fingers, make small balls of the peanut butter mixture, then roll them in the plain cereal until they are coated all over.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples. In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine/butter, cook apple slices until tender-crisp (about 10 minutes), stirring occasionally.
In prepared pie shell toss in flour, cinnamon, salt, 2/3 cup sugar and apple slices.
(Will be slightly mounded.) Place top crust on pie.
Brush crust with milk and 1 teaspoon sugar after decorating crust.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix together tapioca pudding, Jell-O, vanilla pudding and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil for a few minutes, until thick.
Cool, then add Cool Whip and drained Mandarin oranges.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add crushed cracker crumbs on top if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can freeze this and cook later.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple. Save syrup.
In skillet, brown chicken parts in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add syrup, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy and garlic.
Cover and cook on low heat for 40 minutes.
Add green pepper and pineapple chunks.
Cook 5 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Combine cornstarch and water; gradually stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and pecans and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix together confectioners sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Mix well the puddings and milk and spread on cheese layer. Top with remainder of large container Cool Whip. Garnish with grated chocolate bar or nuts. Refrigerate one hour.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pat on top the butterscotch chips and chopped nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then add topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buster bar
directions: Crush cookies well.
Mix with butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread ice cream (softened slightly) over crust.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze until firm.
Combine evaporated milk and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 8 minutes.
Cool completely.
Pour over ice cream and peanuts.
Freeze.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour chicken broth over bread crumbs in a small bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add bread crumbs mixture; mix well. Put in loaf pan; bake for 1 hour, or until juices run clear.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine
macaroni,
bell
pepper, onion, pimento, soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and 1 cup of the cheese.
Put into lightly greased
baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 to 1 cup cheese over the
top.
Bake
at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creole egg casserole
directions: Chop celery, onions and bell pepper; saute in butter.
Add tomato soup and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms, mushroom soup, chili powder, salt, pepper, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer about 5 minutes.
Slice eggs and place in a casserole; then cover with sauce, cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Microwave first 4 ingredients to boiling for 5 minutes.
Stir and pour over Rice Krispies.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Do this quickly as it sets up really fast.)
Frost with melted chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook bell pepper and onion in 1 tablespoon oil until done, but do not brown.
Beat eggs; add crackers, mushroom soup, squash and then cooked onion and bell pepper. Dot top with butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° or 400° until brown on top.

title: saucy baked beans
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir together beans, syrup, onion, green pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and frankfurters until well mixed.

title: minestrone
directions: Heat oil in large pan; saute onion and garlic (3 minutes). Stir in celery, carrots and potato.
Add tomatoes and stock. Flavor with salt, bay leaf and oregano.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Return to a rolling boil and add pasta.
Stir and cook for a couple of minutes.
Add chickpeas, zucchini and basil and continue to cook (5 minutes or so) until pasta is cooked.
Stir in Parmesan.
(Have more Parmesan on table, to be added if desired.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pie cake
directions: Melt butter and
chocolate
together.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased
pie
plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Similar to
desserts served at "The North End.") Serve with ice cream.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Start oven at 375° and grease shallow baking dish.
Put both kinds of bread in large mixing bowl.
Pour 1 cup water over bread and let soak for several minutes.
Drain off excess water.
Mash bread fine with a fork.
Add meat, finely chopped onion, chopped parsley, cheese, slightly beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Mix and form into a loaf.
Put dots of butter over the top and bake 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over the meat; sprinkle with oregano and continue baking 20 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Wash and core apples.
Do not peel.
Fill crock-pot with sliced apples.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Put on top of apples.
Don't stir.
Fill crock-pot to top with more sliced apples.
Repeat with 1 cup of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon. Don't stir.
Let sit overnight.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done (does not shake and a golden brown).
May have to cut the oven temperature down toward the end of cooking time to keep crust from getting too dark.

title: velvet custard pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly add the scalded milk. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 475°
for 5 minutes. Then at 425°
for 10 to 15 minutes or until set and knife in center comes out clean.
This pie never gets watery.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil for 10 minutes, turning occasionally. Drain.
Add all ingredients, except pasta.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve hot over hot pasta. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil until done.
Take couple pieces of potato and mash with fork until they are liquified.
Mix powdered sugar and potatoes until forms a doughy ball (should be firm).
Sprinkle flour on wax paper.
Roll dough ball out thin. Spread even layer of peanut butter over dough.
Roll into log; cut into thin slices.
Put on plate and refrigerate until firm.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Slice squash and mix with all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange sliced peaches in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Heat in oven while preparing short cake.
Mix flour, baking powder, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt.
Add shortening and egg.
Stir well.
Spread dough over hot peaches.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together and spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: mozzarella scalloped potatoes
directions: In shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer half the potato slices, half the onion, then half the cheese.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Lightly sprinkle dried oregano or Italian seasoning over each layer of potatoes.
Repeat layering.
Stir bouillon mix into boiling water.
Pour over potatoes and cheese. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender and crust is golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, sugar, margarine, milk, pudding mix and vanilla in large bowl until well blended.
Pour into shells and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, onion and bread crumbs.
Beat eggs.
Add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add to crab meat. Shape into cakes.
Fry until brown.

title: stuffing
directions: Saute celery, onion, parsley and 3/4 cup margarine.
Add sausage.
Mix stuffing, stock and eggs; toss lightly until completely moistened.
Spoon into turkey cavity.
Rub turkey with lemon juice and 1/4 cup margarine.
Roast according to directions.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Cut up cheese into approximately 1-inch chunks.
Combine all ingredients; mix with potato masher.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Cook broccoli. Season with butter.
Arrange chicken and broccoli in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup, curry powder, mayo and lemon juice. Sprinkle grated cheese and bread crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust as instructed.
Mix water, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook on high heat until dissolved.
Add crushed strawberries and cook until thick.
Paint pie crust with cornstarch mixture.
Add rest of strawberries and cornstarch alternately.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend ingredients and spread on 1 package of English muffins, halved.
Cut each half into quarters before heating.
Heat at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate-covered coconut balls
directions: Mix oleo and milk; beat well.
Gradually add powdered sugar. Stir in coconut and pecan halves.
Roll mixture into small balls. Place on cookie sheet in freezer for 1 hour or refrigerate for 3 hours.
Melt chocolate chips and wax over low heat.
Insert toothpicks into balls and dip into chocolate mixture.
Yields 100 pieces.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Combine croutons and cheese in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs; add milk and seasonings.
Pour over crouton mixture in casserole.
Crumble bacon over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until eggs are set.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and pumpkin together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan and bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour or tube pan for 1 1/4 hours.

title: schamm torte
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites with salt, baking powder and cream of tartar for 10 minutes, until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar gradually; add vinegar and beat 10 minutes more.
Add vanilla and pour into 9 x 13-inch or 2 round 8-inch pans that have greased bottoms, not sides.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Stick in Schamm Torte mixture once oven has been preheated for 20 minutes.
Turn off oven after pan has been in it 5 minutes exactly.
Leave in oven 5 hours or overnight.
Spread with Cool Whip, then a layer of strawberries, raspberries or bananas.
Top with more Cool Whip.

title: egg custard
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs, sugar and flour in medium size bowl.
Add evaporated milk and melted margarine. Mix on low speed.
Pour into pie plate and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches in
a greased 9-inch baking dish.
Pour cup of sugar over peaches
and mix until sugar is melted.
Mix rest of ingredients and
beat well.
Pour over the peaches and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place water in bowl.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Add sugar and mix until smooth.
Can be used in any recipe.

title: delicious meatballs and brown gravy
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and let stand for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
This will allow the Worcestershire sauce to soak thoroughly into the meat.
Roll the mixture into balls approximately 1 1/2-inches round.
Preheat a large frying pan (medium heat) with 2 to 3 tablespoons of vegetable oil.
Place meatballs into the heated pan and brown thoroughly.
Remove from frying pan and
repeat the process until the entire meat mixture is gone.
Let stand in baking pan until the gravy has been made.
Clean frying pan and prepare to make gravy.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together sour cream, soup and butter. Add onion, salt and pepper to taste, hash browns and cheese. Pour into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle cornflake crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter loaf cake
directions: Blend sugar and peanut butter together.
Add egg substitute and beat well.
Mix in baking soda, salt and 3/4 cup flour.
Add buttermilk and remaining flour alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into oiled and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 60 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix with mixer.
Pour into casserole dish.
Warm in oven. Before serving, you can sprinkle nuts on top, if you like.
Serve with crackers.

title: delicious bacon wiener bits
directions: Will also need 1 box toothpicks.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Mix. Sprinkle over vegetables. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ranch potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender (quartered); can leave skins on. Set aside.
Combine sour cream, dressing, bacon, parsley and cheese.
Place potatoes in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour mixture over potatoes and toss gently.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all together, except walnuts, cherry and parsley.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts; put cherry on top.
Garnish with parsley and serve with assorted crackers.
Freezes well.

title: triple cheese log
directions: Blend 3 cheeses together and add nuts. Shape into logs, then roll in chili powder.

title: sweet potato cashew bake
directions: Prepare and cook whole sweet potatoes in salted water.
Drain, peel and cut crosswise into thick pieces.
Combine brown sugar, cashews, ginger and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drain peaches well.
In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half each of sweet potatoes, peach slices and brown sugar mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt leila's jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat the eggs lightly and stir in milk and cooking oil.
Add liquid mixture to cornmeal mixture and stir in corn and minced jalapenos.
Add cheese and onions.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until mixture looks like wet sand.
Beat in eggs well, then beat in chocolate, vanilla, baking powder and cinnamon.
On low speed, beat in flour. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into balls and roll into confectioners sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes or until tops are puffed and cracked.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: thousand dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk.
Boil rapidly (rolling boil) for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to keep from burning.
Take off stove and add broken Hershey bar, chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour on greased pan (13 x 20-inch).
Pecans can be added.

title: yum yum dessert
directions: Stir together and refrigerate. Can make 1/2 recipe.

title: gardener's potato salad
directions: Cut hot potatoes into thick slices or wedges.
Combine vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour half over hot potatoes, reserving remainder for later.
Toss potatoes and dressing.
Cover and refrigerate to chill and marinate.
Meanwhile, steam cauliflowerets and asparagus separately just until tender-crisp; refrigerate to chill.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Brown meats, onion and green pepper in heavy skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into 2-quart buttered casserole or baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Top with grated cheese.
Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Place 1 cup butter, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Using a large wooden spoon, mix together until well blended.
Add eggs 1 or 2 at a time, mixing after each addition.
Alternately add flour and water in which the yeast has been dissolved.
Mix after each addition until the dough forms a large ball.
Cover and let rise in a warm (85°) place for 4 hours or until dough has doubled.
Place on a lightly floured surface and knead gently 4 or 5 times.
Divide into 4 parts, knead each gently and roll into 12-inch circles. Using a brush or spatula, cover each circle with butter.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Beginning at wide end, roll up each wedge and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Let rise 1 hour in a warm draft free place.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: kielbasa appetizer
directions: Put in a crock-pot for 3 hours on low, or put in a casserole in oven until sauce is bubbly, on 350°.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, salad oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and foamy. Stir in pineapple and zucchini. Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, nuts and raisins.
Gently stir into first mixture just until blended.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and cheese custard
directions: Discard large leaves and tough parts of stalks.
Wash.
Split stalks into halves or quarters so they will cook quickly.
Cook flowerets and stalk pieces in small amount of salted water until tender.
Drain; place in shallow greased casserole.
Beat eggs. Add milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix. Pour over broccoli.
Set casserole in pan with about 1-inch of hot water.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Break eggs in a bowl and beat.
Add milk, sugar, salt, vanilla and butter; stir. Pour over bread and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick and easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix in bowl, flour,
sugar
and
salt.	Mix
in boiler, margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix and
add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: white frosting
directions: Beat ingredients on high for 4 minutes. Store in refrigerator. Bring to room temperature to frost.

title: microwave oven-fried pork chops
directions: Coat chops with coating mix according to package directions. Arrange chops rib end toward center in paper towel lined 8-inch square dish.
Cover with wax paper and cook at Medium for 6 1/2 to 8 minutes.
Halfway through cooking, turn chops over.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: miniature reuben's
directions: Spread half of the bread slices with mustard.
Top with a folded piece of corned beef, covering the bread completely but not extending over the edge.
Spread about 1 teaspoon sauerkraut over the meat.
Place 2 thin slices of Swiss cheese over sauerkraut; trim edges even with bread.
Top with remaining bread.
In a large skillet, melt 4 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Saut sandwiches over moderate heat.
Do not crowd.	When underside is golden, turn and brown other side.
Add additional butter as needed.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cream cheese and blend until cheese is dissolved; may heat mixture in microwave to speed mixing process.
Add crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix well and sprinkle crushed pecans on top.
Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: impossible bacon pie quice lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon and onion in pie plate.
Blend remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender on High or 1 minutes with handmixer.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400° and bake until knife comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar-free spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 1 teaspoon per 1 cup hot water.
Contains per serving: 0 grams fat and less than 2 calories.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Blend in flour, milk and boiling water and beat for 2 minutes. add eggs, vanilla and almond extract. Beat 2 more minutes. Fold in blueberries and spoon onto greased regular size muffin tins lined with muffin cups. Bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes, If using fresh blueberries, sift small amount of flour over blueberries from settling to bottom. Yields 48 muffins.

title: beet, potato and egg salad
directions: Layer potatoes, beets and eggs (except one) using salt and pepper and vinegar each layer.
Fry bacon; crumble on top.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Spread on top of each layer, then decorate top with egg, sliced.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries (partially thawed), then next 3 ingredients.
Pour half of mixture into bowl or mold and let jell.
Spoon sour cream over jelled salad and pour remaining mixture on top.
Let jell and serve cold.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Bake for 1 hour or simmer 20 minutes on stove top.
A hearty dish on cold winter days.

title: potato wedges
directions: In a 12 x 8-inch microwave dish, mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Microwave on High 30 to 45 seconds.
Wash potatoes and cut into wedges, unpeeled.
Add to oil mixture. Stir to coat all sides.
Cook, covered, on High 15 to 18 minutes. Stir twice during cooking. Discard oil mixture before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread taco sauce on top of this.
Finely chop onion and green pepper; add as next layer.
Add shredded cheese, then dice up tomato for last topping.
Chill and enjoy!!
Good with nacho chips.

title: cheese potatoes in foil
directions: Slice potatoes. Lay on large piece of foil. Sprinkle salt and pepper. Crumble bacon over potatoes. Add cheese and onions. Dot with butter. Wrap loosely and seal with double foil. Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: nifty nibbles
directions: Note:
Never out of fashion, these old favorites are welcome offerings with cold drinks or just as something to nibble on before dinner.
This may be served with crackers or rounds of toasted French bread.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Mix sugar, Bisquick, milk, water and egg; mix well.
Then add the rest of the ingredients in a tube pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll out on pastry sheet and cut out desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Decorate as desired.
Great with powdered sugar frosting.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise, pimentos, lemon juice, water chestnuts, salt and pepper.
Add peas and eggs and spread into a pan.
Add layer of cheese.
Add crushed potato chips.
Cook 25 minutes at 400° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green wonders
directions: Cook and drain spinach (do not add salt).
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Shape into balls and freeze on a cookie sheet.
When frozen, place in freezer containers.
To serve, place frozen balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pork chops.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, molasses and egg together.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into mixture.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes.
While still hot, sprinkle with sugar.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: hot bean dip(vegetarian)
directions: Layer in the order given. (Olives can be either under or over the cheese.) Bake at 350° until bubbles appear around the edges. Serve with chips when sauce is hot.

title: chicken-shrimp casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken breasts on bottom of greased baking dish. Top with shrimp and artichokes.
Saute onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Melt remaining butter and add flour.
Whisk and cook for 2 minutes (I do it in microwave, easier).
Slowly add warmed milk, stirring.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Stir in tomato paste, Worcestershire and wine. Pour over chicken mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spinach and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach and combine egg, sour cream, milk and first 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Add cheese, drained spinach and spaghetti.
Bake in 10 x 2 x 6-inch casserole for 15 minutes covered at 350°.
Add rest of Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered for 15 minutes at 350°.
Then uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes or more.

title: macaroni and tomato juice
directions: Bring to boil 1 quart water in pan.
Add macaroni to boiling water.
Bring to boil while stirring.
Cover and turn off heat. Let it set for 10 minutes; drain, then rinse.
Put macaroni back into pan and add juice, water and butter.
Heat through.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You can also use orange, cherry or strawberry Jell-O.
They all make a good salad.

title: pizza rye snacks
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Season with onion, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cheese to meat and stir until cheese melts.
Spread on rye bread; put on cookie sheet and place under broiler until hot.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Take 1 slice bread and spread jelly on it, while smearing it on hands, shirt, table and floor.
Put peanut butter on other slice of bread, same as jelly.
Smash bread together and eat with a large glass of milk.
Then call Mom to clean up mess.

title: grandma's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, margarine and milk.
Add flour, baking powder and soda to liquid ingredients.
Mix just enough to make a creamy batter.

title: rolls
directions: Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Grease top; let rise. Knead and make rolls.
Let rise again and bake in 350° oven until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce and sit in potatoes and cheese.
Put in shallow dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put rice in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soups and one can of water and pour over rice.
Lightly salt chicken; dip in melted butter.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice and soup mixture. Bake, uncovered, for about two hours at 275°.

title: chili
directions: In a large pot, brown beef and drain grease.
Add soup, boil 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy but delicious fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit together in bowl.
Mix well.
Sprinkle in dry gelatin.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crisp cucumber pickle
directions: Combine lime with 2 gallons water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Soak 12 hours or overnight in enamel ware.
Remove cucumbers from lime water.
Wash 4 times in cool water to remove the lime.
Soak cucumbers 4 hours in ice water.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spice that is tied in cloth.
Bring to boil.
Drain cucumbers and drop in mixture.
Bring to a hard boil.
Let set 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Bring cucumbers back to a boil for 30 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars.
Boil lids for 2 minutes before sealing.
Place jars in hot water.
Cover the jars and have about 1-inch water over jars.
Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from hot water.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then coat with crumb mixture.
Reserve remaining butter.

title: grilled meat loaf and potatoes
directions: In large bowl, combine ground beef, 1/4 cup steak sauce, bread crumbs, egg, pepper and onion. Divide mixture and shape into 4 - 4 inch oval loaves. In small bowl, combine remaining steak sauce and margarine and set aside. Over medium heat, grill meat loaves for 20 to 25 minutes and potato slices for 10 to 12 minutes, turning and brushing both occasionally with steak sauce mixture. Sprinkle potatoes with parmesan cheese; serve immediately.

title: rhubarb mandarin crisp
directions: In a bowl, toss rhubarb, sugar and tapioca; let stand for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with the oranges.
In a bowl, combine oatmeal, butter, salt and flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; sprinkle evenly over oranges.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve with ice cream if desired. Yield:
12 servings.

title: blair's brown rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put dry rice in a 2-quart baking dish. Slice butter and spread over rice.
Add beef consomme soup.
Cover and bake one hour or until liquid is absorbed.
This recipe is easy to double or triple for larger servings.

title: deviled crab
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Mash the crackers and put half in butter for topping and half in mixture.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt
butter
in
baking dish.	Combine milk, sugar and flour in	mixing	bowl.
Blend well.
Place fruit into baking dish. Pour batter over fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli 8 to 10 minutes (should be crisp).
Then cool. Blend olive oil, garlic powder, lemon juice and mayonnaise together.
Pour over cold broccoli and blend.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate. Combine with sugar and oil. Add eggs one at a time; beat well. Add vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to chocolate mixture. Stir in nuts. Chill dough. Make into a small ball and roll in *powdered sugar. Place on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on rack. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: meal-in-a-bowl stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add beef broth, corn, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with tossed green salad and French bread.

title: coca-cola bayou gumbo
directions: Cut fish into bite size pieces and place in a large pot.
Add all the ingredients except salt, pepper and rice.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in bowls for serving and top with heaps of rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Preheat browning skillet 4 minutes in microwave oven.
Melt shortening in skillet.
Brown meat strips.
Arrange meat in center; put sliced vegetables around the outside of meat strips. Combine sugar, soy sauce and bouillon and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Vegetables will be tender, but crisp.
Serve with rice.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Add pineapple and mix.
Lightly grease baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and remove all moisture. Drain water chestnuts and slice very small.
Chop onions and crab meat very fine.
Then combine all ingredients and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: hot rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and shortening; let cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast and let dissolve.
When yeast dissolves, add 2 cups of flour at a time, beating real good after each 2 cups. Let rise until doubled in bulk, then roll out and let rise again. Bake at 400° until done.
Spread tops of rolls with butter.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Cream in egg. Mix dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture. Add rhubarb and fold into the dough. Spread into an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Combine pineapple and cream cheese.
Mix in remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick.
Add sugar and beat thoroughly.
Add milk and vanilla and mix.

title: laura's coconut pie
directions: Place butter in a bowl.
Add sugar, beaten eggs and flour; mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well. Stir in coconut with a spoon.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pie pan (9 or 10-inch).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: You will also need canning jars and lids.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well and set aside.

Beat eggs; gradually add milk, syrup and vanilla, stirring until blended. Gradually stir egg mixture into sweet potato mixture and pour filling into pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool; serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In large bowl, combine gelatin and boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in mashed berries and bananas, pineapple and pecans.
Turn half the mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Keep remainder at room temperature.
Stir sour cream and spread it over strawberry mixture in dish.
Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream layer.
Cover; chill for several hours, or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: "willsburg cream of peanut soup"
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Stir in flour until well blended.
Add chicken broth, stirring constantly and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and rub through a sieve.
Add peanut butter and light cream, stirring to blend thoroughly.
Return to heat, but do not boil.
Serve, garnished with chopped peanuts.
